comment: Absent in discussions and very hard to access outside of class. An expert in his field and challenges you to interpret the course material correctly while also applying it at multiple levels. Reading heavy, however, the information learned will translate to any criminal justice field. Great class, just don't expect a lot of interaction.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Newmann teaches the class as well as could be expected for such a dense subject. The material is definitely not easy, and his jokes are definitely not getting better. (but they're so horrendous they transcend into hilarious)  Homework is insanely tough and absolutely requires reading the book, but the tests lead very simply from the homework.
One of my all-time favorite professors. The material is challenging, but Dr. Newman is very helpful. His jokes are getting better, too!

BEWARE - she is definitely the worst prof I've ever had. Her handwriting is terrible, so couple that with her completely disorganized lectures and you're on your own. Had 4 group projects that were basically the same exact project over and over except with a new set of data each time. All projects are in R but she used another language in class!!!
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Group projects--Tough grader

comment: There is no pre-requisite for coding but you definitely need it. She expects you yo know and doesn't offer much help. No homework, there are quizzes every week, 4 projects that require coding through R, and two exams. No textbook required.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy--Tough grader

comment: Not helpful at all when asking for help in office hours. Her class isnt that hard though.

Her class could have been better organized, but her class is not hard. She posted notes for each lecture and answers for each quiz on WebAssign. They were so useful to prepare for the midterm and final exam in her class. Make sure you review them thoroughly if you take her class.
Some students say that projects are not related to materials we learn in class. They probably did not notice how closely they can be related and how useful to learn from each project.

She's extremely scatter-brained.  The content isn't difficult, but she's so unorganized and all-over-the-place, it's difficult to understand what's going on.  The lectures/quizzes/projects/exams don't particularly relate to eachother either, which makes it difficult to learn.

This class was very appropriate for me in my chosen major, but it is also a really great way to learn time management, document creation, and group work skills.  There are a few lengthy reading assignments, but learn how to skim for answers. He encourages that.  Also be aware that he may assign reading due on the first day of class.

I'm not a big fan of English classes typically, but Jordan made this class great. If you're struggling, see him for help. He is willing to help and further explain things, so take advantage of it! He assigns a lot of reading, reading reflections are daunting, but overall they help improve your understanding of rhetoric for sure.

His class is easy but him as a teacher he is terrible. He is very pompous and arrogant which makes me never want to ask a question or ask for help or even talk to him for that matter. I will never take a class of his again. His class was easy, however it is difficult to have a hard English 101 class. Pick a different teacher.

He is one of the easiest professors I have ever had in my life. He starts out super annoying and stays that way -- always laughing at dumb things. His assignments are helpful but his office hours I really dreaded -- if you give him donuts he'll give you bonus

This class is incredibly easy. It's an easy A if you do the work and listen to his advice. He is really nice at first, but then he gets a little annoying. He doesn't take responsibility for messing up on assignments, and your grade can take the toll for that sometimes, but it's never too significant.

Mr. Loveridge was an awesome teacher, he was very clear and went over things slowly to ensure everyone understood, graded all the assignments fairly and gave many extra-credit opportunities for those who missed homework assignments. Literally the easiest A I've gotten
Awesome teacher. Gets along well with students and treats everyone with respect. Funny guy, pretty laid back. Willing to help during class or office hours. Definitely recommend.

reasonable teacher. always prepared for class and tried to make it interesting. only he's pretty full of it and his laugh is extremely annoying. if you can get over those things though he's an ok choice for a 101 teacher
He is a great teacher, very helpful in his office hours and always willing to clarify if someone doesn't understand. He is also entertaining.
Very helpful, all assignments are clearly laid out. He is extremely willing to offer help and advice when ever needed. Funny at times, fun class overall.

Pretty good teacher. Attendance is mandatory, but the assignments have reasonable due dates, class is canceled the week of big essays (which is helpful), and hes reasonable when accommodating emergencies. Class is interesting too, never really dull.
He is an excellent teacher. Thats all you need to know.
He moved to the Georgia Institute of Technology, and this man is amazing. He has a grounded sense of humor with fun logic and enjoyable judgment in all he does. Best professor this year.
Gives students an opportunity to participate, and share their opinions.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Professor L was one of my favorites this year at Oklahoma State. We had reading homework about every other class which was fairly easy because we were never tested. We only had 4 projects. Every class started with personal conversations among the class about the weekend or exciting events going on. Would highly recommend
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Would take again

comment: He loves to engage the class, so if you are capable of participating, participate.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: Teacher made English interesting and made me genuinely enjoy going to class each day. There were small 250 word papers due once to twice a week based on reading assignments and 3 larger project due spread out through the semester with the longest paper being 6 pages. Participation is a must and the teacher will count how many comments you make.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Would take again

comment: Clear about grading requirements, lectures were interesting and engaging. Quite a bit of writing expected every week, but he always provided thorough feedback.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria

comment: Dr. L is all right. You absolutely have to show up to class or you will fail because there are participation assignments in class. We had to write like 500 words a week which was kind of a pain but it's only for like 6 weeks. If you don't like reading or don't like participating, don't take him, but if you want a decent class, take him.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: this class was the hardest thing I have ever done. Had to read 30 page articles written in the 1500s and the write a 300 word analysis every night. He takes attendance exactly when class starts and if you're aren't there on time he will mark you absent. Felt like I was in a much higher level English class. NOT RECOMMENDED

He assigns a reading and a 300 word analysis of that reading every night, articles can be up to 30+ pages long and were written in the 1500s. His students are never right, he is very belittling if you try and share your opinion. For the papers, we had to perform science experiments and write on them. Leaned nothing about english from this class.

Be prepared for reading.. ALOT. There is usually three to four homework assignments each week, but they are very easy to understand. He explains his papers very clearly, but it wouldn't hurt to go to his office hours. He does grade very hard, and only a couple people in his class ever got full points on his homework. ATTENDENCE MATTERS!!!

He is a very difficult grader. I would not recommend taking his class unless you are and English prodigy. Analytic journals responses from an article reading are due online every two days (article may be 30+ pages). Again, very tough grader, highly recommend using office hours and asking him for help. Average class grade is accurate.

He is a super hard grader and he shows absolutely no mercy when grading. You have to be excellent at Grammar to get a good grade on a paper. However If you are taking his class. Go to his office hours and write your papers with him. Office Hours with Professor L. are extremely valuable. He will break everything down and  help you alot

Professor L is a VERY hard grader! It is extremely hard to get full points on any assignment. This was the only b I got this semester, the rest a's.  There is an assignment due every week. I hated going to class, I do not recommend taking this teacher.

I think that ASU should be aware of this professor is one of the worst professors I had this first semester, he wasn't very helpful on anything. to be a Eng professor he didn't communicate clearly on anything. His links to send blogs were always not working, TERRIBLE teacher. The worst I have ever one person placed the same comment 3 times on here

Professor L is a great teacher and is very clear about what is needed in class. My class was a hybrid class which was a little odd on how it was set up. He did his best to try all of us as well. He also emails back very qucikly which is hard to find nowadays in college. I love Mr. L! He is a difficult grader but just listen to what he wants.

The workload for this class was quite substantial. We were required to write 1,000 words per week. However, he was very helpful. The hybrid class set up was not great, because we were only required to come in once a week. However, the workshops were really good. The professor was a nice person, and a very fair grader. I recommend taking his class!

The workload for this class was quite substantial. We were required to write 1,000 words per week. However, he was very helpful. The hybrid class set up was not great, because we were only required to come in once a week. However, the optional workshops were great. The professor was a nice person, and a very fair grader.

This class was the only one I struggled with my first semester. I took the half in person half online class and it was so hard! Even though there was just 3 essays he graded them really hard. Class isnt very helpful, what is helpful are the workshops but if you can dont get this type of class! He is also strict on attendance!
This was easily the most difficult English class I have ever taken and definitely the hardest of my freshman year. The expectations are ridiculous and the workload is huge. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS

I forgot what the book is called because I don't really read it, but it's kind of a hard class if you take it with this Prof. He's kind of strict about attendance. There's only four absences allowed then it's an automatic fail. If online homework is late, it's counted as an absence. Good luck. I also had no clue what the homework was supposed to be

This was the worst class of my life. I am an art major and was forced to take this drawing class, even though i cannot draw. She was constantly moody. She didn't grade on how much I learned, she just graded on your skill level, even though this was a 100 level class. Horrible do not take this class.

Assignment instructions are clear.Gives individual attention to students.Participation is fundamental, be there!She challenges you to do your best;even though you may curse her(and yourself)for pushing you, you will thank her in the end.Her passion for art, teaching, and knowledge of the subject has each student wanting to impress. A+ Recommended!

I'm not sure if she's a genius or just simply insane. At first, I thought the class was hard. I didn't like to draw either.  But, she has a way of getting inside your mind and teaching you. Shes always talking about drawing whats inside you and stuff.  Like really reaching into yourself and making art. I'd recommend her at least once.
Muchlinski is brilliant. He is super helpful if there's anything you need to go over in further detail. Would definitely recommend.

Slides are very text-dense and straight from the books. He then reads the slides to the class. Speaks in a monotone with run-on sentences and very little space between sentences. This class could be so interesting but his teaching style makes it difficult to stay focused.
Great instructor and definitely knows what he's doing. He is a great painter and gives helpful feedback. I'd definitely take this class again
Loved his life drawing class
Ben is very understanding and knows a great deal about contemporary painting. Would def. take his class again!

She is very kind and helpful. She listens to the class and moves due dates to accommodate more time-consuming projects. The projects are always interesting and fun. You have to read a chapter from the book every once in a while, and you sometimes have to work on projects at home. The class itself is very laid back.
Great instructor. Clear instructions. Good feedback. Helpful, caring and positive. Wants her students to succeed. I would definitely take another class from her.

Good instructing, always clear on what we needed to know for assignments and tests. The material was sort of dry, and she did a really good job of summarizing the applicable concepts. Approachable, helpful, nice, and understanding. Would recommend her and take another class with her.

This professor is more concerned with APA formatting than with social work. There are literally "APA Challenges" attached to every essay that you will write. I would take the class with anyone else if I had the choice.
she gave lots of homework every single night. extremely hard grader
Ms. Chan is a strict, but helpful teacher. She grades a bit tough but her comments make sense, and are easy to improve upon.

Such a wonderful teacher. You can tell she really knows her stuff, and she enjoys teaching it! On top of that, she's so sweet, and the most fashionable person I've ever seen! Definitely take her class if you can :)

Dorothy is a boss! This is her second semester teaching and she really brought her A game! Her classes are exciting and fun, but it definitely depends on class participation and attitude. She gives a lot of homework compared to other English teachers, but it's not too much and you really learn a lot from her. I am impressed!
rachel is crazy. take her!

Rachel is by far one of the sweetest, nicest, more caring English teacher's I've ever had. She really cares about you doing well in her class, and wants to get to know everyone of her students. She makes class fun and exciting. I never dread going to this class because it's something new everyday. Definitely a good professor to have for English.

Rachel is the most amazing English teacher I have ever had. She gave criticism and knew what she wanted out of your essays, but she also really cared about your success. This is definitely an easy class with an added bonus of a quirky and awesome teacher. Take it!!

Rachel is a great professor! There are a few essays to write throughout the semester but she is 100% clear with everything she wants from you.  Overall one of my favorites, she's very funny and always has relative hilarious stories.
Rachels cool and eager to teach class everyday. She prides herself in becoming close with her students and involving everyone during class.

The best professor I've ever had! She is funny and relatable and extremely helpful. Workload isn't too bad, a few essays. Cancels class when we have essays due so we can meet with her one on one. Keeps the assignments interesting. Favorite class by far! DEFINITELY TAKE HER CLASS!!
Very nice. willing to work with you if you need help on things. Good office hours
Dreadful teacher. Docks you points for unreasonable things. Gets upset when things are misunderstood when SHE'S the one who always messes up the students. If she talked less, we'd get more done.

She's a sweet lady but I also feel like she's shady. She kind of expects you to understand everything even though she says it so unclearly. Going to office hours doesn't really help, cause she's rude about not understanding things. She is a very fast grader but a harsh one at that. A difficult class with dry content. I don't recommend her. Sorry.
She doesn't explain well  AT ALL. Even when she grade a paper, she doesn't say what are the mistakes that I did. Seriously a tough graded. I would not recommend you to take this class.
Seriously TOUGH grader.
Loved her! She is so nice and wanted everyone to succeed. PARTICIPATE so class won't be quiet and awkward.

Mrs. V is a fantastic online instructor. She responds to your emails very quickly and is very approachable. If you pay attention to her thorough rubrics and comments on your work, this should be an easy A.  She also offers up to 5% of extra credit! If you need this class, take it with her, it wont get any clearer or any easier.

Very easy class and easy A if you do the work. Don't skip any writing assignments or discussions or your grade will easily drop. Weekly quizzes were easy points. Don't expect an A if you put little effort into it. Read the feedback on papers and you'll see why she docked you points.
couldnt get anything hire than a B on papers... why the heck does she grade so hard... you lose like 5% for one grammar mistake.

I had recieved As in both English 101 and 102 but could never get anything higher then a C on any paper. She grades very harshley and the only things you really get points for in this class are papers.
Super helpful, always makes himself available for everyone, plus a cute accent from new zealand.
Easy A Guarantee!

Hands down the worst class I have ever taken, this is my second MAT class I have taken in college, this is my third semester. I am an AB average student. I completed all of the homework (which is irrelevant to test and quiz work) failed all tests. Even though I did all of the HW, went to every class, I couldn't even receive a "D" for a curve. BS.

The hybrid class is easy if you keep up. The problem sets are for points but aren't that helpful for the tests. Focus on the prep quizzes before the tests because they are really similar. Don't wait until the last day for Mastery points or else you'll drown
Attendance is mandatory. webassign will help you to pass the exam.

SUPER easy! The hardest part with the mastery points online is typing in the answers wrong. But after a few weeks, you get the hang of the website and how to enter everything. He and the TAs were always helpful. You have a chance to get ahead in the class, do it! The tests are JUST like the practice tests. Have unlimited tries for Mastery points .
When I had asked for help on anything, he was extremely rude and spoke to students in a condescending way. I would never take this class again. AVOID THIS TEACHER
Attend class and study and you will do fine.  Teacher was always willing to help.
Horrible style of teaching. Not a very pleasant guy

I can't believe so many people leave negative feedback. Prof Fox is extremely helpful. He gives more than one example for each type of questions. He could even check your answers for your in-class quiz before you submit. I could get an A+ if there were one.

This teacher does speak fast but he is also extremely helpful, cares about his students and will go out of his way to help-as long as your willing to help yourself.    I highly recommend this professor.

Worst teacher I've had in my entire life. He talks too fast and it is impossible to keep up with him during class. The tests are very difficult, mainly because he never taught me a single thing. Do whatever you can to avoid this teacher.
Hard work, perfect homework and extremely hard exams. Finally I got C+.

To be honest, I skipped his class a lot, but when I actually attended it was not that difficult. I had a B but after the second test I dropped to a 54 in the class. I got a B on the final exam which left me with an F but he bumped me to a C. Not too difficult if you take notes. He is willing to help if you attend his office hours.
Do yourself a favor and do not take this teacher.  If he is the last teacher available, wait till next year or clear your schedule so you can learn calculus on your own time.

This class was the hardest class I took this semester. I busted my ass and studies for at least 20+ hours for the final and got a 60% on the final bringing my grade down 6%. All he does is ramble and show useless examples and never really explains anything conceptual about what he is doing. He is  obviously very smart but DO NOT TAKE THIS TEACHER.

I wasted a semester of school and a semester of my life because of this class. Too much homework that counts for too little and isn't relative to the test or pop quizzes. Yes, I did say pop quizzes. This guy who can't teach very well gives out pop quizzes. Pop quizzes consist of everything from the last quiz to things he hasn't even taught yet.

If you are inclined towards mathematics or are willing to actively participate then Professor Fox's class is manageable. Yes, he talks rapidly, but his examples are helpful and he is clearly knowledgeable about the subject. My biggest complaint is his inability to control the class. Extra credit is available for completing assignments early.

do not take this class. fox is not a good teacher, he does not teach new material in step by step process, but rather does example after example without stopping and explaining on he went from step to step, he also teaches you the homework questions the WEEK AFTER the homework is due. he does NOT OFFER EXTRA CREDIT OR ROUNDING AT ALL

This class is impossible! The professor speaks quickly, gives difficult pop quizzes, only 3 test (which make up most of your grade), extensive homework every week, and presents lectures that are irrelevant to test and homework. You spend so much time doing HW due every week (even test week) that it becomes difficult to study real test problems.
I'm so dissapointed in Arizona State after taking this professors class.

Honesty,he's a nice guy. But as a teacher he's awful. He does examples on the board to and expects us to follow along which is near impossible with the way he explains his steps. He "teaches" us sections from the homework after they're due and even with practically living in the math center I'm boarder line passing this class. AVOID AT ALL COSTS

do not take this class, no extra credit, all he does is look at the whiteboard and do examples and does not stop, not a good teacher, does not prepare you for exams. take any other teacher but this one, there are 3 exams worth 25% each, online homework is 15% and 5 pop quizzes are worth 10%

One of the worst teachers I've ever had in my life. He talks so fast no one can understand him, and he never tells you what section he is on. He will teach the Webassign homework/section the class after they are due....Does that make sense? no. Nice guy but horrible, horrible teacher.

The professor is a nice guy, but his teaching pace is way too fast and its easy to see the frustration that this causes in the students. I'm blown away by how the teacher can hand out pop quizzes when his class is struggling. If you ask him to repeat something, he gladly will... but there's so much he needs to repeat with such little time. Awful...
I think that anyone who says pop quizzes are a gift loses all credibility. Especially at the difficulty of these particular pop quizzes.
I wish this teacher could teach
always willing to help(:

Mr Fox is probably the best thing since sliced bread. His lectures are so clear and he makes calculus sooo fun and easy to learn. He gives three exams (he did a great job preparing us for the first one) and the pop quizzes are simply a gift. This man deserves a prize.
Terrible Teacher- teaching style is horrible and he never teaches material worth knowing for homework and exams. If he does, it's in a format that is not easy to learn from.
Sitting through this class is like listening to Beez in the Trap on repeat. I have to retake this course.

He is not at all helpful and doesn't appear to mind or maybe doesn't notice that most of the class is struggling and needs him to take the time to teach the subject. He stands at blackboard and talks 90mph to himself while we try to figure out what he's talking about.  Doesn't finish before moving on to next section.  Impossible to pass!
If you like listening to mumbo jumbo then  you will like this class.  If you want to learn something and get a decent grade, you will not like this class.
He forced me to listen to Wrecking Ball. He puts a few things up on the board with no explanation with what we are to do and then kicks it in the back.
I wouldn't even recommend this teacher to my worst enemy.
This teacher is horrible! Completely fails to explain anything, and on the rare chance he does, he talks to fast to understand. Can't learn anything in this class.

DO NOT TAKE MATH WITH THIS TEACHER. He is brand new and has no method to teaching at all. Everyday he does a few problems on the board without even telling you what section he's going over and speaking at a rapid pace that no one understands. You're grade is based on two midterms, your final and a small portion of homework. Worst class ever!
Amazing professor! I had him for two semesters at GCU. ENG101 and ENG105. He gave great feedback and I always got As.
Easiest class you will ever take. Entire class is three essays and that's practically your whole grade. No final, no tests
He made something as dry as ENG 101 very bearable. He has no tests and isn't a hard grader. Take his class!

Took his 101 class and it was fairly easy. Just go to class, participate, and turn in your things on time and you'll get an A. He's a nice understanding guy so any one who has a problem in his class and anger problems.

Really great professor and person. Had the entire semester laid out the first day. you write 3 essays and work on them in discussions so really easy. If you go to his office hours on edit day he will peer edit your paper, then make those changes and you're guaranteed an A! Only complaint is he refuses to give anyone a perfect score.

Mr. Hohner is a really nice guy who urges students to attend his officer hours if they need any help at all. His lectures were very boring to me, but I was very uninterested in the content. There were like 3 essays and each essay question was like an essay within itself--kind of confusing. He wants a lot participation, but he had no success.

Took this class to fulfill a literacy requirement, wish I hadn't. His lectures are SO boring, but he takes attendance for 20% of the final grade so you need to go. Exams are easy and come right off the study guide, 2 essays are required but they're not that bad, he's a relatively easy grader. Easy A if you go to class but you'll be bored to death.

Super awesome guy! Really cares about his students and is always open to meet outside of class or talk before the lesson. He does his best to make the lectures exciting and engaging and made a lot of interesting assignments that were more exciting than what the normal WPC 100 classes had to do.

Rhett is one of the best professors I have ever had at ASU. He truly cares about his student's success and well-being. His in-class material is entertaining and straight to the point. I would recommend every student take his class. RHETT ROCKS!

Rhett is a dope dude. Such a nice guy. His class is really easy, and honestly pretty helpful if you're looking to be an entrepreneur. You aren't going to learn anything ground-breaking here, but you will have a nice chance to connect to the resources on campus that can help you! Also, class was very manageable, and there was little to no homework.
Great Professor Willing to help you out! Very Understanding!

Rhett is a nice guy and he introduces some interesting topics in this class. The course content is a bit disorganized and relies on a group project. Nothing too difficult. Just show up and do the work. He is fairly accessible and cares about his students.
Super nice teacher. Super easy assignments. Do the work and you'll get an A. There was a big group project which was annoying because I ended up doing all the work but it still wasn't bad.

Trujillo is a great professor. While he does not exactly explain what he expects with assignments, he doesn't grade to harshly. As long as you put the effort, you will do good. Don't forget the weekly reading quizzes as they are worth 5 points each. He is willing to work with students and is super cool to talk to. Definitely recommend.

Not sure what the two poor reviews are about. Rhett is probably the most laid back professor I've ever had. . I will agree that I'll feel very confident in a 100% report and get an 85%, but to actually do poorly kind of speaks to the character and work ethic of some students. Group projects are a little annoying but usually very easy.

Worst teacher I have ever had. He graded half of the semester the day grades were due. Even if you do everything he asks in an assignment, he still marks you off points for no reason. You can not get a perfect score on anything. I took his online class.. there is no book, so he basically makes things up as he goes. he also lisps in  lecture videos.

Super laid back professor and a really easy class. There's a few group projects but their relatively easy and he assigns groups for you. Takes a while to grade papers, but you'll probably get an A on it anyways so why worry.
Rhett is a good teacher, takes awhile to grade the papers but a good teacher.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Rhett was very laid-back and extremely accommodating.  He kept class interesting and while attending class is definitely necessary, he was really helpful for the instances where I was sick or out of town. He's awesome to build a relationship with, and will offer guidance long after you finish his class. Amazing professor!
He is a helpful teacher, and will go out of ways to help you out but he is also a tough grader. He makes the lectures interesting and you will actually learn from this class.

I loved his class! Originally signed up for it because it fit my major. I have learned so much just by doing the easy assignments. I spent maybe 30 min to an hour a week on homework. 3 part end of the semester team project like mentioned before along with about 5 team projects throughout the semester. Easy class to get an A!Chill and easy going too

I took this class as credit filler. The topic is interesting but it gets extremely bogged down with the ridiculous amount of busy work you're required to do. I had three assignments this week. Not worth it for the credits (since I don't need the class for any other reason).

Very bad professor. He's extremely arrogant and egocentric. He liked me, but I saw him verbally abuse someone during class for disagreeing with him. His TA was even worse, especially when he says he's skipping lab because he doesn't feel like teaching, and lies about your grade when you ask him. Entrepeneurship is great, but this class isn't.

super easy class!! group/individual projects throughout semester. easy homework, all online "journals". very good professor, unclear at times for group porjects, but wants you to be creative and innovative.  two short easy books, no tests, final is 3-part group presentation. very easy going and understandable. definitely take if you need an easy A.

I loved this class. Rhett is an awesome teacher and the material is really great. Lots of projects but they are not the projects will do in any other classes- they are for the purpose of practicing and increasing creativity, it is refreshing! Take it! (I also had the professor for 294 and it was great too- but totally different [394 is better])
His class was a lot of fun, and very different. There are a lot of team projects and individual projects but fairly easy. I would definitley reccomend this creativity class to anyone.

Class was heavy reading and split up into two week chunks, youll have a quiz on each section and a discussion which youre required to respond to other students. Theres a few papers based on watching videos or going out and interacting with people from cultures other than your own.
super easy class, gets a little boring but definitely easy. The textbook says required but you definitely don't need it to get a good grade.
Dr. Wong is one of the best professors I've had at ASU. Her lectures and grading criteria are very clear, and she always presented the matieral enthusiastically and passionately.

I really enjoyed this professor. She was really nice and sweet, made her lectures very easy to follow (she does not post online). If you keep up with the work, which isnt a lot & is fairly easy, you should get a B & above in this class. If you miss class more than allowed, she will have a talk with you to see if anything is wrong. Great professor!

She is a wonderful professor. She gives feedback on every assignment and responds asap if you need to ask her something. I took this course online and she made the class very easy to follow and super fun. You learn all about leadership styles in this class. You have weekly quizzes, assignment , and a weekly virtual meeting. Take this class!!!
Very nice professor. She is at Downtown campus now, doesn't teach at Tempe.

Professor Wong was one of my favorite professors so far. She is very caring and wants to help you pass. There was only two tests and no final. Her grading material is clear and if you follow it you will get an A. I definitely recommend her for COM1OO and would take this class again if I could.
She is very caring and gives great feedback. She is very strict on her rules so just show up to class and do what she tells you to do and you can actually get (100) in this class.

Dr. Wong is so sweet. She's very knowledgeable and I wish I could take the rest of my COM classes with her. If you're struggling she will totally help you out, just show her they you care and want to succeed in her class. She talks kinda fast and has an accent, but overall she's a good teacher.
She is very helpful and responds quickly to e-mails. As long as you read and review course materials and post to discussion boards promptly, you should not get less than a B average in this class! :D
Horrible professor, useless course.

This class is fairly straightforward. The lectures are long and boring, but the tests are easy if you take notes during class and study those notes. Professor Wong makes her expectations clear from the start of the class. My biggest issue with the course was her not understanding students' questions or answering them in a way that really helped us.

Took Terrie for COM 100 and got an easy A. The class itself is long and boring but the tests are easy as long as you stdy and she is an extremely sweet lady. Just go over your notes and the tests are easy as pie. The only thing is an a+ is impossible because you have to get a 100% to get an A+

She is such a sweet lady and really cares about what she teaches. The class is boring and easy and most of the content is common sense stuff. The tests are a little tricky but overall a really good class. I would recommend it for sure :)

AVOID CLASS AT ALL COST. Wong is an alright person, although her exams are HORRIBLE. Exams are 25 short answer and you must know the whole definition word for word. I went in to talk to her about my test grade and she admitted I got the answer right but told me she would only give me 1/2 a point because she didn't understand it.

She was a good teacher overall she made sure you knew the material However her tests are short answer and she is by far the worst teacher when it comes to grading that I have ever had I'm used to getting As and I'm only want a C in this class She wants better than memorization if she thinks you don't understand what you wrote she wont give points

Professor Warble is very nice and easy to get ahold of. She does have a tendency to baby the students for sure. There are usually 2 assignments a week. The labs are super easy and usually last about an hour. There is also no textbook needed, all the content is given by her. The class was fairly easy but expect a lot of classwork.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Accessible outside class--Get ready to read

comment: I suspect that Ms. Warble's curriculum is designed to address a problem at many universities: failing physics is a driving cause of dropouts. With that in mind, it's easy, but in a good way. Her course comprehensively breaks down the physics misconceptions you probably still hold, even if you took it in high school. Just be patient, do HW, get A.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria

comment: Easiest class I've ever taken, my freshman year of high school physics class used some of the same labs. The prof kind of treats everyone as if they are kindergartners - we used "privacy folders" during tests. She is super nice but honestly her personality rubbed me the wrong way. The TAs were cool though

I found her lectures and explanations confusing at times. This course feels more like a high school physics class than college. Labs are a joke and never take the full time. In terms of science classes, definitely an easier choice. I liked the course, but I also like physics. If that's not your thing, I would find another course.
Prof Warble is pretty amazing. She really cares about her students and actually attempts to make the material interesting and easy to understand. Her TAs and LAs are really helpful as well.

Very nice prof. and a pretty easy course. She teaches it fairly well, and her TAs were great. Tests were fair, huge amount of points came from the 3 tests, 2 quizzes, and weekly labs. Showing up to lab is 20 points and the lab itself for each week is 80. As long as you ace the lab section and do well on the exams you will do fine.

Her lectures are difficult to follow.  She doesn't answer any questions directly and she doesn't teach anything.  She expects her students to teach themselves and figure it out.  She rarely inputs grades.

She is very helpful and clear on what she expects on assignments and exams. Formal lab reports can be tedious, but she doesn't grade too tough on them. Gives a lot of homework, but there's no extra reading and few notes need to be taken. She posts all Prezis online and often gives answers on homework before turning it in.

She was okay.  She's very friendly, and she would email us the answers to our homework the day before it was due.  But she emails it out around midnight, and every single answer key had at least 1 wrong answer on it, so you would be confused when it came to the exam.  Also she was really unorganized this semester, but its because sheshasmoreclasses

She's a very nice lady, and extremely helpful during office hours, but this class is a real pain in the ass. The homework assignments are so tedious. On the exams, the multiple choice is pretty straightforward, but the written calculations part can be challenging. Unless you already took Physics in high school, you're in for a struggle.
teacher is super nice and willing to help with anything. Class is very easy. no textbooks. definitely take for easy science credit

HST 337 w/ Sweet is mostly writing papers based on the 4 books that she chooses for the semester. Honestly, you can skim the books but you should have them. Over the course of the class, be prepared to write 40-50 pages in total. But beyond the papers, the class is fairly straightforward - No real homework, no real exams.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--SO MANY PAPERS--Tests? Not many

comment: Dr. Sweet is passionate about the topic and she put so much effort in creating the PPs. I enjoyed her lecture because I love Native American history . You would learn a lot about the topic but here were my issues: there is a lot to read and even more to write. 3 short papers and midterm/final take home (each 4) essays + a 15 page research paper.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--SO MANY PAPERS--Clear grading criteria

comment: I felt like I was taking a 7th grade history course taught by someone who had taken an 8th grade history course. She gave no feedback on essays and used the same prompt for each paper, therefore getting mad when you basically wrote the same paper each time. I thought she was a horrible professor and I learned almost nothing new.

Nice teacher and the material is straight forward. I bought the textbooks for the class but never used them and ended up selling them back on amazon. Only bought them for the online code you need. She committed to offer feedback to me on an essay but never gave it to me. Overall it's a pretty easy class, show up, take notes, and do the essay easy A

Prof. Sweet is very enthusiastic and very nice. Attendance was not mandatory, but you'll miss the notes because she doesn't post them online. Two major essays, she gives you topics and you choose. Exams consists of multiple choice, short answers, and take home essays. The take home essays were short for both midterm and final. Quizzes every Friday.

Prof. Sweet was really quite a disappointment to my entire schedule--- she lectures EVERY day, and gives you no information about what will be on your test(s) besides all the information that we have gone for the 1st half, or the 2nd half.  The exams are partially multiple choice, and exam, although you can expect a bad grade since its so diverse.

She's an okay teacher, goes through material sorta fast. If you miss class you miss what she has on the power points because she does not post them. have 2 major writing assignments that are not hard if you pay attention. She tries to have to class interact. She'll tell you if she doesn't know a word and laughs at her mistakes. Very informative.
GREAT professor. Calc 2 has an infamous reputation, but the way he taught it made it seem easy. He's also hilarious in a deadpan sort of way.
If you ask, he answers! went to his office hours for some hard webwork questions sometimes and he either decided they were too hard and took them off or helped me through it. Great teacher.

Cares for students. First few lectures may seem like he's super boring but the more you talk to him about your questions after class or before class, he's very easy to connect and will take the extra step to teach you until you understand the material. Great professor and I will take him for MAT 267 if he's available!!

He comes in and puts up questions on the board 30 mins before class, has students go up and do them, and then grades them as if they were exam questions.  He also has review sessions for each exam.  Insanely helpful and actually cares about his students.  Average grades were high, even without extra credit given, great guy.
I had a tough time with Professor Korytowski. His lectures are not only long, but not clear enough. Would definetly suggest taking some other professor at ASU.
Best teacher ive had. the class is fairly easy as long as you participate and ask questions. Funny guy and easy to connect with.

The main thing i liked about Daniel was that he taught the material very clearly. As far as lectures go he was one of the best professors I have ever had. The downside is that he is a hardass when it comes to grading. He will take large amounts of points off unless you solve the questions exactly as he does in class even if you do it correctly.

Best Math teacher I have. Be sure to finish every webwork as much as you can, and ask question no sooner the class is end. Don't delay every single question, which may accumulate to big issue. Anyway, I get recommendation letter from him finally. There is no good and bad teacher. What's most important is yourself-----from your ideology!!!

Calc is hard. Korytowski makes it slightly less hard. Webwork for homework (yay for infinite guesses!), exams are part MC and part FRQ. Doesn't curve, but will spend hours trying to help you understand what you are confused about. Cares about you if you care. Withdrew because I couldn't keep up with 18 credits, but am re-taking him next semester.

He's extremely helpful, and will spend eons making sure that you understand whatever you have trouble with. You just have to ask. There are quizzes every Friday, and Webwork (AKA infinite tries) due every class, but the homework load is only 5-10 problems per class. I'm terrible at math, but he made sure I did as well as I could.
Slightly better than the average Math professor. He's great at helping students that have questions.
well ,he can be your friend and teacher,both at the same time. prbably one of the best teachers at ASU
Wright knows C++. If you want to know C++, you want to know Wright. CSE394 is the only class he teaches though :(

Excellent instructor that will spend much of his own time to ensuring you understand and complete the material. Gives ample time to complete assignments. Also, he knows a ridiculous amount about programming in C and C++. He even helps students that show up for his office hours that aren't enrolled in his class. Class is very helpful for CSE majors.
One of the best teachers I've had. Really cares about her students and will help anyone succeed in her course if you ask questions and attend class. I really enjoyed this course.
This class with Darcy was one of the easiest i took all semester and she is a big help if you don't understand the information the first time.

Professor White is a good teacher. She is clear with her expectations, as well as with instructions. She is not helpful, however, when you have questions- preferring you figure it out on your own or turn to your group for assistance. She is fair and willing to work with you.

Darcy is an amazing teacher.  She really helps you in training before going to the school.  The elementary students you tutor and teach are good kids.  Darcy is extremely bright, and she always impressed me with new ideas.  You will get to work with Mrs. Klem as well, and she is excellent.  There are also a few papers to write.

Professor White is an outstanding teacher. She is patient with her students and takes the time to make sure everybody is getting the material. She is fair with assignments and homework is light/minimal. Take her classes - she is simply the best one out there.
Hard tests, grades harder on homework. Horrible professor. Avoid avoid avoid!!!!

This professor was pretty average. Not super interesting but not awful either. The tests are pretty easy but the homework is graded pretty harshly. You are expected to show up to all classes. She teaches straight from the book so if you are confused you can just read the book.

Love this professor so much. Her lectures are always interesting, and she really helps you understand the material by using examples from her personal experience as a clinician. She's really funny too. Finally a college class where 90% of your grade is not based on tests.
She is a great professor who wants to see you succeed.  Her lectures don't put you to sleep and she is always willing to meet with you. Do the study guide and you'll ace the exams!

Dr. Pedersen is the best! Her lectures are extremely interesting, and they make me want to go to class. Exams are not difficult if you complete the study guide well. 6 small assignments, 4 exams, clicker points. TAKE THIS CLASS IF YOU WANT TO BE A PSYCHOLOGIST!
very easy course - I took it online and accelerated and got an A. just make sure you read the book and watch powerpoints and you will be fine.

One of the easiest/least challenging classes I have taken, even being such a high level course. Just go to class so you can get the participation points (usually just a paragraph worth of writing). Got 100% on both the midterm and final. She makes the information very easy to understand. Definitely take her.

Great Professor! She has long lectures that you need to watch, but I took the 7.5 week course and got an A, pretty easily. A quiz pretty often and a writing assignment (not long) every week! Easy if you watch her lectures!

I loved Dr. Pedersen! She is amazingly helpful! If I emailed her she would email me back very quickly and was always ready to help even though it was an online class. The structure of the course is awesome because it gives students a way to actively participate as well.

This was a good class! It was challenging, but not too difficult with some studying. I got A's on almost every assignment. There are a few paper and 2 oral presentations. The teacher was very nice and cared about our feedback about the class and implemented changes.

Dr. Pedersen is a great teacher! Go to class because she does clicker points!  She asks for a lot of student feedback about the class so that she can teach in a way that's best for the class which was really helpful.  Lab is easy just stay on task and go to class. overall good class

Dr Pederson is a great professor! makes class interesting and cares about students,and their comprehension of the material. If you go to class and participate it is impossible to get a bad grade.students who do not like her are the ones who don't come to class or don't pay attention in class. I would take another course from her without hesitation
Really nice! The content is pretty easy.  Random in class "ticket-ins" for attendance points.  Lectures are kind of slow moving.

Very committed to helping students succeed.  Requires some work but no more than any other class of the same level.  Learns every students name and is willing to edit papers before you turn them in.  Replies to emails within minutes most of the time.  Overall great professor and would recommend her class.

Dr. Pederson genuinely wants to help students and is reasonable about the structure of the class. e.g. she will send out multiple surveys and ask questions in class to ensure that the students are getting what they need to do well. Boring material though.

Great instructor! She cared so much about every student and would do anything to help you succeed in the class. Reading the textbook and going to class are necessary since clicker points are every day. The course material can be dry but she makes it the best it can be by adding interesting research and class discussion. Highly recommend this course

I've never had a professor who catered to and cared about her students as much as Dr. Pedersen does. The course material was boring, but she made it more bearable by including current research analysis and videos. Ample opportunity to succeed assuming that you're willing to actually work. The grade you get is the VERY reflective of the work you do.

Great instructor! I would highly recommend. 4 exams. The questions are exactly like teh study guide. Lots of participation points every class & tons of extra credit toward end of semester. She teaches everything very clearly and PowerPoints are posted online. Easy A given taht you do well in lab.

Best teacher ive had at ASU.  Actually cares about her students, learns everyones name.  Tests where easy if you just reviewed  the chapters.  She really made all the papers that we had to write stress free.  She also asks the students what they want to change about the class, then she actually makes changes! i wish i took all her classes.

I'm not sure why all these comments are so negative. Dr. Pedersen was a great teacher. She is invested in making sure her students succeed and she tries her best to make sure that we are all enjoying the class. Tests are fair and papers are relevant.
She was really nice and helpful. The lab section is a lot of work. The class overall isn't bad.

She is poor at teaching and explaining, reliant on the book, and either bitter or expresses a lack of knowledge about the subject - though students have to band together to force her to answer questions, because she prefers to speed through rehearsed slides. Her answers tend to either be insults or "it's in the book."
She is absolutely horrible. Her class structure is terrible and she doesn't have a single clue how to teach and be remotely interesting. Avoid her at ALL costs.

She knows what she is talking about and very professional. She grades hard on the essays. I suggest giving her your paper in advance to receive feedback. She is hard, but it is useful if you actually apply it. Tests are fairly simple. I only missed one point or two on all the exams, and lost most in the papers. But still got an A.

The class is interesting, but the professor is the worst I have ever had (graduating with a 4.0 this semester). Well, this class might be the ONLY B I receive at ASU. I haven't received my final grade yet, but this teacher is rude, unhelpful, and condescending. DON'T TAKE THIS CLASS!

I hated this class with a passion! She was a very hard grader on your papers (4) and never really gave you feedback on how to improve. She nit-picks everything and says she wants your feedback on her but she doesn't care to change. Wouldn't take her again. The only thing I liked was her study guides for the tests. And you have an oral presentation.

At the beginning of the semester I thought I was going to fail, but she listened to the students and changed up the course to help us learn. Props to her for that. The subject was boring and it does take studying outside of class to pass but hey, you didn't come to college expecting a free pass did you?

her class is hard. she is really open to making her students happy though. the beginning of this course i was mortified but she changed her teaching style and way of testing and it was awesome. lots of work. dont go to college if you dont want to work hard though

1st comment is right on! papers are graded fairly (by the TA!) Test are hard and I studied for the class more than any class before it and my highest grade on a test was a 72% In class activities are useless busy work. Have a question the answer is ALWAYS "It's in the book." Not a friendly person either! DO NOT TAKE HER!

Worst professor ever! Exams are all over the place so you don't know what to study, though she claims the study guide covers everything, it doesn't. Must go to class as she gives 2-5 in class points. Not willing to help and shows no interest in her students well being. Grades very hard on papers! Stay away!!!

Avoid her at all costs. She is entirely reliant on the book, she goes by pre-planned lectures with no concern about the class unless it flatters herself. She has no concept of different learning styles and tends to answer questions with "it's in the book." She always has excuses, but rarely answers.
Poor teaching skills. Disorganized & ambiguous grading on essays.

I'm not saying that Anita is the worst professor in the psych dept at ASU, I'm just saying every other professor is better. Don't take if you don't have too. Plays favorites big time. Grading is arbitrary as earlier mentioned. Just take anything else

Honestly one of the worst classes I have ever taken. She was NEVER prepared, grades were arbitrary, and the tests were completely disorganized (even though they were directly from the textbook and fairly easy). Her lectures added NOTHING to the class, but were still mandatory and had a big impact on your grade

Four tests, one make up exam optional instead of final. Tests consisted of multiple choice, fill in, and short answers. I rarely used my book, always went off her study guides and notes to prepare for the exams. Lots of small oral presentations (groups and solo) and four papers. If you consistently put in the effort you will do well.

might have been her first semester teaching. She is very smart but subject of class was boring. Takes simple information and make it challenging in hopes to make the class more interesting. The way she words questions on tests is confusing. Overall, nice lady who needs to work on teaching methods. If you use your common sense you'll get an A.
Good Teacher. The tests were challenging and made sure you had a thorough knowledge of the material; sometimes questions were worded a tad ambiguously. Very helpful and approachable.
Dr. Yong is the best college professor I have ever had. He teaches and works like a machine.

Personally this has been the best math professor I've had. I took his class for Calc 1 and 3. Let me say, the Calc 2 professor didn't hold a candle to Yong in terms of clarity and the amount of example problems he gives. Plus he is a lenient on grading free response questions which is always a plus.

I always thought Calc was my strong suit till I got this guy. Turns out i just had good professors before taking him, and my grade was low this semester. He ends up making all the material real confusing to understand, atleast to me. Never really tests what we covered in class or in hw either, so I had to essentially learn most of the material .

Tests are different from homework. Homework can take hours so make sure you have planned your time. Usually follows close to previous exams. Easy quizzes for attendance, which with homework is 25% of your grade. Lectures are not so clear.

He gets a bad rap from everyone here. Yes, he is quite unorganized and often pauses during lecture to gather himself. Yes, his in class lectures don't always cover the homework. BUT, what he covers in class is what is on the test. The tests strictly follow the test review and practice exam. He gives a quiz daily asking things like "what day is it".
Doesn't seem to care whether students understand anything. Often doesn't know how to do homework questions that he assigns us.

He is unbelievably unclear. His lectures are  boring and are nothing based on the homework. The homework is completely different from what he teaches. Easy quiz points, but those aren't much. Extremely difficult tests as well.

Young is a laid back professor and I enjoyed his classes but isnt the best at explaining concepts and constantly makes mistakes on the board but he will try his best to help you understand material and go over it with you. Tests were straightforward he also takes attendance by giving a ridiculously simple quiz at the end of each lecture

He is not the best teacher.  He writes everything he says on the board and sometimes it can be hard to understand.  Homework is all online and test are easy.  I've never taken any calculus before and I got a B in the class.

One of the worst teachers I ever had in my entire life. His explanation is poor, gives an easy quizzes which makes us not to study our lessons every time, some of his tests are difficult. NOT RECOMMENDED AT ALL. STAY AWAY.
I took calculus before, so calc 1 was super easy for me. Yong writes every single detail on board. Homework is only WeBwork. Tests are fair. Good teacher

This is the 3rd time I've taken this class. He's been the best.  No accent. Takes attendance with quizzes during class.  Isn't the best at explaining. I recommend using wolframalpha and youtube videos.  Subsribe to integralcalc, the girl on there is awesome at explaining everything you need for this class.
Awesome educator!

350 words can't express the goodness of Yong.He is the best teacher I ever had.He just has some online homework and you have limitless attempts.He has some quiz in the class but they are so easy that it is hard for you to make a mistake.If you listen to her carefully in the class, you can easily pass the exam. I got 100 in some exams.
good guy. just listen and you will pass
Lacking social skills. No accent. Horrible at explaining.

No accent. First year teaching, so he is still trying to figure out how to teach. Really chill, gives cookies when he makes mistakes on the board. Writes every word on the board so there ends up being paragraphs instead of math problems. Tests are harder than the examples, but still not impossible. Final was really easy.

He has no accent and teaches straight from the book so he doesn't have many examples. His notes are sort of clear to understand so if you miss a class you can just get the notes. His tests are 17 questions and one from each section. They aren't very hard but he makes simple things difficult to understand. He can be lazy when it comes to questions.

He doesn't have an accent which is nice, but he has zero speaking skills and is terrible at making things clearly understandable. I had to copy his notes exactly and refer to them later to try and learn anything. All homework is online so don't get the book.

While he has no accent (huge plus), his lack of public speaking skills makes his lectures very difficult to follow. I have no doubt he knows what he is doing, but has a very hard time getting his point across clearly. I never bought the textbook as hw was all online. He's a pretty cool guy, just needs practice organizing himself and his thoughts.

Has no accent, something hard to find in ASU engineering courses. Takes time to explain all the steps and explains them in a very easy to understand way. Took calc 1 with him and very bummed he won't be teaching calc 2 next semester.

I took Understanding the Brain as a GPA booster, and it ended up being my favorite class of the semester. The class is insanely easy if you keep up, but I actually learned something which was really exciting. You can tell Stamm is very into her field of study and it is encouraging to experience that throughout the course of the semester.

I needed a 1-credit elective and chose this one on a whim. Loved it! The course material is fascinating and informative, and the professor is clearly passionate about the subject. Discussion board posts are straightforward and quizzes are easy. You'll learn some awesome facts about the brain. ASU needs more courses (and professors) like this!

A really easy, interesting class. Every week: one discussion board, one response post, one quiz. The final week is extra credit. Stamm is kind and understanding in e-mails. She is enthusiastic about the material, and picks interesting readings and sites for each week!

Super easy A if you do the work,  a weekly discussion board and response to 1 peer each week along  with a weekly quiz which were cake. If you are needing spots to fill electives take this class, you would be glad you did!!

Dr. Stamm clearly enjoys the topic she is instructing. The people who did bad either didn't show up to class or tried to bs through the reading material. This is a course about understanding how people learn. If you are in grad school for education research and don't take this course seriously, you should really rethink about your future goals.
Dr. Jill is a great teacher and I really enjoyed her class. The work isn't too overbearing, just right. She had guest speakers to help supplement the material we were learning. A+ instructor!

She was very clear and organized which is essential for an online course. Provided excellent material to understanding neurology. She taught the information very well that she made it an interesting class. Definitely would recommend taking her courses!

Dr. Stamm is a phenomenal teacher.  She is knowledgeable in the field, and knows how to apply content to her students' lives.  She is engaging and passionate about the material.  I would recommend her class to anyone!
Take this class! I'm an incredibly poor writer and I got 100% on basically everything. You will get a credit and an A for Reading 10 articles. The teacher and the class are great.

Fun class, and learned a lot of valuable information. If you do the work and give thoughtful responses based on the work you'll do well. I snug by and pulled an A, but she can take some time getting your work graded. Fun teacher though. Interesting class.

One of the nicest, most helpful professors I have ever encountered.  Loves the topic of the class, and her enthusiasm spills over to the students.  To this day, I find that I use the things I learned in her class more than any of the others.  Great professor and great class.  I would take more from her if she taught more that applied to my program.

Rhonda Phillips is one of the greatest teachers I've ever had and her class, Happiness in Society is a highlight of my college experience. Her classes are fun, easy, interesting, and inspiring. Everyone I know who had her for any class feels the same way. Plus we take field trips- MIM, Sedona, Venice this semester. Better than having the day off.

Disappointment is the best description my experience. This class made me truly appreciate my previous math professors. We spent too much time going over entry level examples and not problems that we had to complete for homework or tests. During office hours, he'll just repeat the theorems taught in class or tell you to look at your book.

Dan is a great instructor. He is very approachable if you have questions that need answering. You will need to study just like you will for any other class. Calculus can be difficult but he is good at explaining it. He also gives a lot of examples in class, which I found to be very helpful. If you put in the time and effort, you should be  fine.

Mr. Weinstein was so helpful. He made math class worth it because he was such a great professor. His lessons were easy to follow along with the book and he is very easy to approach, especially during office hours.

Worst teacher ever. He is a grad student that relies on theorems a lot. Not that helpful during office hours. He does know math, just not how to teach. Its either his way or the highway. He teaches straight out of the book, so there are hardly any variety of examples. If he is not in a good mood, he will say, and you can tell.

The worst math teacher I have ever had. As a student who loves math, I was very disappointed. He knows what he's talking about, but he doesn't know how to teach it. Even when you ask for help, he rarely actually clarifies. Avoid this class unless you have a HEAVY Calculus background and a lot of free time!

The worst math teacher i have ever had. He gives tests that none of the other classes are required to take. He gives tests right after breaks and he is not good at teaching the material. He knows his stuff but he is a horrible teacher.He does not go over the material that is confusing enough and spends way too much time on simple concepts.

So it's a very easy class but there were two time where she was not clear on the syllabus and the dates where screwed up and made it hard to understand. Her email responses are bratty when I asked questions. Kind of made me feel dumb when i asked for clarification.

Two chapter quizzes and reading journals every two weeks- very easy as long as you actually read the book and put thought into your journals and answer all questions! Besides the readings and the journals, there's CPR certification and a short resource guide that you have to make with information from the textbook. Easy as long as you put in effort

I took her online course and she's a really easy professor. There's 2 reflections and 2 quizzes due every 2 weeks. The quizzes are very easy if you read the book and the reflections are always relevant to real life. She is very clear with what she wants you to write about & WILL dock you if you miss something but otherwise, she's very nice & easy.
Great Professor! :)

Professor Bass is an outstanding/excellent Professor. She is very caring and kind. She will always make herself available to students. She believes in enhancing your knowledge. She has a very skillful way of making the most complicated assignments seem simple. You will learn a lot from taking her classes, and you will also enjoy the experience. :)

Amy Bass is an awesome professor. She gives you so many opportunities for points and to demonstrate your understanding. Statistics is hard for many people, but this class made it easier. Do the practice problems in the lectures, read the book, and watch the videos/ powerpoints. This is an active learning class. Put in the work and you'll do fine.
Assignments were not graded on time. It was usually a two to three week turn around.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: I have never received a grade below a B. However, this class changed that. The expectations for the discussion boards are unattainable. Besides that, as long as you read your books- you'll pass the quizzes.
I am glad I took this class. I feel I learned more than I did in some of my classes this eacher really teaches. The assignments were intense but she was very helpful and I learned a lot.

I took this class online and she was all over the place. Her syallabus and instructions were unclear. I know APA pretty well, but she continued to mark off for minor things and than get upset when you asked questions via email. I dropped the class and took Ms. Hickle online who I love. Don't take Ms. Bass.
Great teacher and great class. Be prepared or you will fall behind. You have to really wok in this class but its worth it.

Her explanations of assignments and essays are all over the place.  I had to try to translate between the difference of emails, posts, and revised course calendar to figure out what she wants.  Then I email and she doesn't get back to me for days and it was an internet class!

Uses videos watched at home as the lecture. Works problems in class. Basic easy problems in class and on review but hard problems on test. Being able to do the problems on the review doesn't help you pass the test. Loves fractions. No calculator.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Prof. Geisel was an okay professor. She would sometimes get upset with students when asking questions not only in lecture, but in office hours as well. It was hard at times to communicate the different areas at which some of the materials did not make sense. Taught a little to fast for some students to understand.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Unorganized, can be very condescending! Lots of projects?! Lots of homework, review and lecture consists of easy problems, tests consist of hard problems. She's nice at times, but once she learns your name be prepared to be constantly called on. Even if you didn't raise your hand, or even if there wasn't a question asked.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: literally one of the hardest teachers in my life. was no help when approached for help on material you don't understand. exams make up huge chunk of grade (60%) so if you don't do well on them like me, you won't pass. ended up with a D even with tutoring!  beware of LOTS of homework! have to retake the damn class now when I'm a psychology major smh

This professor teaches to the test! You get 2 attempts at each exam and unlimited attempts at homeworks and quizzes. Also lowest exam score, quiz score, homework score are all dropped at end of course! If you suck at math, your chances are better taking Professor Geisel!
ratingTags: Participation matters--Clear grading criteria--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Honestly do yourself a favor and do not take Math with professor Geisel.  She is not organized and does not know how to instruct a class appropriately. I earned a B in this class and it was because I basically tough myself.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: If math is your worst subject, you can get an A in this class.  I've never earned an A in a math class in my life but I got an A- in Sonya's class because the opportunities are there to succeed.  Unlimited attempts on quizzes. Exams are much shorter, easier versions of the quizzes.  Do quizzes over and over to practice  you're golden
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Clear grading criteria

comment: She is a horrible teacher and is terrible at explaining things do not take her if you struggle!!!!!!!!!11

Math is not my preferred subject, I have always struggled with the topic however she was the best teacher I've had. She always answered every question I had. I failed all the exams and still passed w/o taking the final. Quizzes unlimited attempts, Exams 2 retakes. Drops 1 exam 1 quiz & 3 homework. textbook opitional

Professor Geisel's teaches a different method of doing things, the "easy" way.  Follow her lectures and ask questions and you will do good.  Quizzes are long but the exams are easy if you study your quizzes.  She invites you to ask for help and responds fairly quickly.  I usually do not like math but I found this class "enjoyable" for a math class.
No

I hate math but this class was easy. This professor lets you know exactly when everything is due. You don't need the book and can save money just buying the pearson code. She gives SO many chances to get a better grade. You get to retake all the quizzes and exams so if you fail it's on you. Encourages and teaches to use the calc. Great professor!

Great teacher and class, but you really have to work at it. She loves teaching the "easy" way with the calculator instead of using formulas. Listen to what she teaches, actually do the homework, and you'll get a fair grade. Don't be afraid to ask questions. Very willing to help and a fair grader!

I had to comment on here about Professor Geisel.  She is the opposite of rude.  She is sweet, helpful, and she sincerely cares about her students and she is very helpful to those who need it.  I can't believe some of this crap that I read about her on here.  If it wasn't for her help, I would have failed, only because the material is very difficult

Not her fault calc is just hard to grasp for a lot of people. Occasional tutoring, reading asking questions practicing, this class is passable.  No time to teach thoroughly with the class time she is given. Teaches the basics and what she can. Takes her own time off to meet with students.  Received B- and I failed 2 of 5 tests.

Worst professor. She only taught the basic problems and gave difficult ones on hw and exams. I practically lived at the tutoring center, met with her one-on-one for hours weekly, did every assignment/ review guide, studied for days on end, had weekly study groups in the library and still failed her class. Recommend taking at CC if you want to pass.

Alright so I took her class thinking I would be okay cause I had taken calculus before. Boy was I wrong. She is a terrible teacher! Worst of the worst, I got help as much as I could I did everything possible to pass her class is literally impossible, avoid her at all costs I mean it.
Skips very important details in the material, shows lack of proper understanding of material, gives false information from time to time
Offers help, though you're better off at the tutor center.

I took Geisel for MAT 210 and it was definitely one of the worst classes I've taken to date. Not only is she blatantly rude, she also gives very difficult exams. Homework and Quizzes are given regularly but the four lowest are dropped. If you are good at math you'll be fine, if not, steer clear.
Only take Sonya if you are ready to fail. She is a terrible teacher.

Failed this class freshman year and there was no hope of passing. Do not take brief calc with her if you are not good at math or have not taken math in a while. Her lectures are a little easy to understand but the homework assignments and exams are much more difficult.

I took mat 210 and I hated it. I failed the class and now I have to take it again next year. Geisel is a nice person but a horrible teacher. More than half of my class dropped out on the dropout and many of the remaining students are not doing so well. DO NOT take this class with Geisel of you want to pass.

Took this class a first time my first semester at ASU, HARDEST class I've ever taken besides chemistry. Dropped it and retook it my second semester, still struggling. I decided to go to her office hours and she helped me TREMENDOUSLY. She will make you work for your grade, but if you show you're trying she'll help you with anything!!

If you're not that great at math, I would not take a class with her. If you are great at math then you'll enjoy it. I'm terrible at math and I really disliked that class. She's kinda rude in class if you ask a question, but if you go to her office hours she's really nice. It's a different math for sure and it's tough.

I struggled in this class but it was a requirement for me. First, unless your good at math you will work  (hard!) for your grade, I easily spent 100 or so hours doing my homework and quizzes. At the least, Prof Geisel will reply to your emails and she does try to help if you ask her. Basically if you put in the effort you can pass!

Teaches too fast. No review for tests. She does't care whether you pass or not. High dropwithdraw rate of students.  Never want her as an instructor again. She teaches as though she is scolding students..
DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS! I can not stress enough how rude and unhelpful she is. Worst Professor! Math is difficult, she makes it impossible.

Openly admits that she won't learn your name. I've had a calculus class before, and what she teaches doesn't connect with what I've learned before. The difficulty isn't progressive, she would barely explain how to do something, then proceed to give us the most difficult question to learn it from, sometimes she won't give you the answer to check it.

she is all over the place, doesnt finish one thing and is already moving on to something else. But great personality, yet I didn't see her  as a good professor due to her lack of teaching skills. Overall, if you go to her office hours she WILL help you, so dont hesitate!!! Glad she was there for me.. also tutoring will be like your best friend.
A haiku: Geisel is the worst Useless, tangent queen, vexing Her class is torture.

She's just a bad teacher overall.  I attended class everyday and the subject still seemed so confusing.  Her lectures are bad and the questions we go over in class are never like the ones on the homework or tests.  You go over really easy questions in class and then when you get to the homework they're way more difficult.

Just terrible, failed her class freshman year and unfortunately got her again when I went to retake the following year. Never goes over a problem with a single fraction and yet expects you to know how to do it on her quizzes.  Instead of dropping lowest quiz score, she gives extra quizzes so you can "make-up" for bad quiz scores.

Geisel is a casual teacher. However, she lacked in teaching skills. And once she teaches you something she expects that you never ask her about it again and won't help you. She is hyper and happy, but she gets off topic too much and tries to buddy buddy with students. I do not recommend her AT ALL. Avoid her if you truly wish to earn an A in MAT210

Take someone else if you can.  The lectures and problems in class don't apply to the homework or the test. If you're not good at math, don't take here.  You'll be doing a lot of figuring out things yourself. Lectures Problems- Easy Homework Problems- Hard

She has an amazing personality and is good as a person but she doesn't know how to teach! i spend most of my time getting tutored.
