Homework assignments are not difficult but she gives quizzes mostly everyday. Also, she is behind on posting homework assignments and sometimes expects you to finish to at a time. Please do not take her.. very hard....

She is funny and nice, just can't really teach in a clear way. Hard to follow along and doesn't really explain the material on the homeworkassignments. Just kind of expects you to apply what you know, which is understandable because that's the point, but it is difficult.
Doesn't round. At all. Isn't clear when you ask for help at times. Does offer test corrections which help your grade

She's a fantastic teacher and will help you along the way. The concept is hard but she is engaging. There's online hw for every section and 4 tests through the year. Fair grader doesn't want you to fail. Just be prepared to study and you'll be fine

Not helpful. Makes things harder then they really are. You're in for a ride with her. Class average right now is about 60%. I asked. Does not curve. Complicates things. Sarcastic. When asked for her help she gives off uninterested/annoyed attitude. Only plus side is she posts test grades the following day.

She is very nice and funny in class. All of the other ratings are low because nobody likes math and all math is hard no matter who teaches it! But she is extremely helpful, she lets you do test corrections too. I went into her office hours and she told me everything that was going to be on the final. Shes a good teacher.
She is a nice person.

DO NOT TAKE HER. She is rude to everybody. She is all over the place when teaching. There is no way to follow her and understand what she really wants. You are not allowed to miss one class either. She does not give anyone time to do the problem and think about it she's super fast and not helpful.

Awful! She is sarcastic, snippy, and doesn't take you seriously if you are not a business major.  She would respond quickly to emails, but she always seemed annoyed that you emailed her. She moved through the material too fast, didn't allow for questions, and behaved as if students should already know all concepts before she taught them.

I took her class at ASU West and having calculus in the morning was rough. But I made an effort to go to every single class. She takes times to go through her power points and explain the examples. She asks the class, which was a size of 40, if we needed further explanation. People would ask questions and she would respond and really tried to help.

Prof pessor Geisel makes the math concepts seem much more difficult then they really are. Her class is one of the toughest classes Igave ever had to take at ASU. Bottom line do not take her class unless you want to spend 10 hours a week doing all the hw and studying.Definitely not an easy class.

If you have a choice when it comes to this class, DO NOT TAKE IT WITH GEISEL. She was rude, confusing, difficult, and unhelpful. She snaps at all the students a lot and is very sarcastic. If you want some help on anything, she won't be nice about it and assumes you should just know how to do everything. She was by far the worst professor ever.

This class was crazy easy. Prof Geisel explained things very well, I never had to use the book, just class notes. She prepares you for the test really well and allows you to make corrections on your test for a few points. If you don't get atleast a B in this class it's becuase your lazy.
She is terrible! Dont take any classes with her!

the wose structured class I have taken at ASU! The tests are half written and half computer which sounds easy, but the computer portions suck because they dont allow for any partial credit. Average computer scores were very low. Dont take if your GPA counts on it or you are not good with math to begin with, YOU WILL FAIL!!

Dr. Singh's class is a lot easier than people give her credit for. Honestly, if you're going into a physics class thinking it will be as easy as a gen-ed, you're going to have a rude awakening. Quizzes are verbatim example problems from the book (12% of your grade right there), and HW is   easy (20% of your grade) Just suck it up and study.
Well it was a rough class. I didn't learn everything from her but I just read the book and stuff! So i guess it just wasnt good.

It was clear that this was her first semester teaching through clarity and grades. A C in this class ranged from like 40%-60%. All of her tests were multiple choice, giving no partial credit at all for at least using the right equations. Physics II is a hard class and she made it so much worse. Thank gosh for my awesome TA. Definitely used the book

It was definitely her first semester at ASU. Her lectures were PPTs based on the book, so class was useless. Generous curve for C's (40 - 60%), but a terrible experience. Only survived because of the amazing TA I had, who unfortunately is moving on to student teaching next semester.

I believe this was her first semester teaching and it showed the first half of the semester.  She wasn't a bad professor, I just think the way the physics classes are structured make it hard to learn.  Multiple choice quizzes sucked, but they got way easier at the end of the semester. I did a majority of learning from the text book.
Her accent makes undertanding her hard. The tests that she makes are nearly impossible and the class average is usually 45%. I highly recomend not taking this professor corvatoo is better.
You got to be prepared for this class, if not you will not succeed. Good TA always there for you.

If you are looking for a TA who will help you better understand lecture material and challenge you, then Joel is the best! He is funny and tries his best to help all the lab students. Easy A if you put in effort into your reports.
Joel is the best TA I have ever had! He is super helpful and even explains advanced concepts clearly. I would love to have him again in any lab but he does make you earn your grade. Get this TA !!!

Great professor.. Provided a lot of feedback for all assignments and made you really understand what the course was attempting to teach. Several papers are required and they really made you apply the text to the writing prompts. Definitely would recommend.

She is a great teacher that truly tests you.  If she disagrees with you, she actually explains why instead of just getting passive-aggressive.  Totally willing to describe things in detail to make sure that you understand.  A great time, highly recommended.

Very ambiguous. She kept stressing for us to think about things that we weren't being taught. Really pushes social justice down your throat. She seems to take it out on you with your grades if you disagree with her. LOTS of reading, a new chapter and at least one article per week.

GREAT teacher, willing to put the time in teaching you the material if you dont understand. Show interest and she'll notice your efforts. I recommend taking her class. Make sure you read the book you pick for your final. or it will be hard to write your final paper.

She is a great teacher, she is getting her degree in teaching. She wants the students go to lectures on campus, make sure you do it. Helps with your grade. She has two presentation: Group & Individual. When she speaks, its alittle boring, but she will help you when needed.

highly recommend professor Hollinger, he makes politics really interesting and is not biased in his way of explaining how the world works. He has an insane understanding of individual countries and offers a unique perspective on everything. He's also extremely understanding and lectures are basically discussions on easy readings. take him!
Overall there was a lot of work but it was all super easy.

Great professor. I am surprised he didn't get 4.0. Very understanding and doesn't give you unnecessary work. The difficulty level is good as well, though you still need to do your assignments which are pretty fair. Would definitely take again and recommend. Oh and many extra credits.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Graded by few things--Amazing lectures

comment: Recommended.

Professor Hollinger has a unique, hands-on approach to learning. His economics module was a simulation. This approach brought greater understanding of the world market, resources, and how economics truly work. His lectures are enlightening, engaging and led to class participation. Great lectures. Truly cares about his students. A+.

Hollinger is awesome! He works out a syllabus with each class individually & is very lenient with course work/due dates just talk to him. Weekly chapter summaries & quizzes but all short/easy. Simulations were cool & a lot of fun. Loved this class & learned a lot. Sounds like he's lived a crazy life/has some incredible stories, seriously cool guy
Really cares about his students. Awesome professor.

This class is only boring if you make it so. Prof. does class discussions, group projects, and case scenarios that involve teams. Majority of the class were anti-social and didn't participate- created a dead, dull, lame experience and that's a shame. I'm shy/quiet and I participated still, it's not hard. Can't blame the prof for students' apathy.
ratingTags: Participation matters--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: I learned a lot in his class, and it opened my eyes to a lot of things going on in the world right now.  He isn't always very clear on when things are due, but he won't knock your grade if you turn something in late (As long as it isn't like a month late).

Good teacher, i dont know how i made it thru, but if u have to take this class, than do what you have to do, but please if you are taking this class because it sounds intriguing and you dont need to take this class because it doesnt count and just trying to get full time status please dont do yourself like this, alot of group presentations tho..

A strange experience. While he's an easy grader, he grades VERY late, so we were sweating the whole time, wondering if we were acing the class or failing it. Stupendously unclear - and retracts his own statements and denies it. (Or ignores you.) Very stressful. An organizational mess, and he was neither very helpful nor interested.
He was extremely disorganized and didn't give directions very well.  Very hard to understand when anything was due. I wouldn't recommend.

I would not recommend taking a class with Dr. Hollinger. He is extremely disorganized, and the absolute opposite of straightforward even when students repeatedly ask for clarification on confusing and often contradictory assignment descriptions. He still hasn't graded anything past the first week of the course and the class ends tomorrow

Taken him last semester for STS 110, great professor so I took him again this semester. Very chill and will work with you on deadlines if you need it. The class can be long if no one participates, so get involved! Comes to class prepared and adds humor to his lectures, will take him again!

Professor Hollinger is cool as a person, but this class was very dry and boring. The assignments were very confusing to the students and their formats are tough. The students had to ask for clarification on them many times. Additionally, it's basically an English class with a lot of written papersassignments. Don't recommend.

I would highly recommend taking Hollinger for this course. I took it online B session (7.5 weeks), and I wish it had been a semester long class. He split the class up into two options which you could choose from. Option 1 was like a normal class with quizzes and exams, and option 2 (my choice) was discussion based with no quizzes or exams.

I love the way Dr. Hollinger taught this class! Group discussions are a big part of his teaching. Instead of just lecturing from slide shows like most teachers do, we got to learn from each other and see things from other points of view. He is always available for questions and is very understanding.

He takes a different approach with his online class work. Instead of just giving you information and expecting a rehash it in a test or quiz, Dr. Hollinger sets up his course to require critical discussion every week in the online discussion board after going through readings and videos. It isn't actually difficult if you put in the mental effort.

I took Hollinger for global technology online and he is not a good teacher!He may be flexible about deadlines and return emails promptly, but that is about the only good thing about his class. TONS of group work, ten page research papers with almost no guidlines, and ridiculous weekly journals. Too hard for a 100 level class!

He is very helpful and replies to emails within minutes! The assignment load is giant. Maybe around 100 assignments per chapter. You also meet virtually every week with him and a partner. Do not procrastinate in this class or you will fall behind fast.

Paul is a great professor, he rejects traditional teaching methods in a sense that he doesn't agree with them and tries to make the standardized tests given easier by providing with the tools you need to succeed. There is a lot of work, mostly the iLrn which is somewhat helpful. The most beneficial assignments were the compositions. A+ teacher.

I was nervous staying in Professor Kidhardt's class because there was nothing easy at first, but I'm glad I did. His class is completely in Spanish, and he uses Spanish articles, news, and movie clips from the real world which are better than the text book alone. You have to work hard but you'll learn a lot!

I was super nervous going into this class as a freshman, but he was very welcoming. He is very helpful and understanding of a student's busy schedule and homework load. Definitely my favorite class this year. Teaches completely in Spanish and is easy to understand and interesting to listen to. I wish he taught upper division classes! Take his class

I really enjoyed his class. He really cares about his students and wants everyone to succeed. Great with communication and responds fast to all emails. Works to help students in anyway he can. A lot of busy online homework but all Spanish classes have that. He gives you the answers after the first attempt with most professors don't do

3 papers and that is it.  So those papers take a lot of time and effort. She gives you a lot of time to work on them with many editing options. Her class is boring though. Discussions are usually about things that have nothing to do with the papers. She always wants to help students, and offers many review options.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: I deeply enjoyed English 200 with Professor Brown, I think she's a fantastic teacher. She genuinely cares about exploring literature with students, and presents the material in a highly organized, theory-driven way. I wish I could take another course with her. If you're prepared to focus in class and do the readings, you'll enjoy the course.

She makes her lectures very interesting by incorporating thought provoking videos and activities into her class. Assigns 3 major papers with enough space between each paper, and also holds EXTREMELY HELPFUL conferences where she basically tells you how to fix the paper to get an A. Go to her conferences, they help a lot.
She is a great teacher! Super nice and helpful. She assigns 3 major papers- as long as you put in the effort she will give you a good grade. A very laid back class.
Ms. Brown was super awkward, but overall not that bad. Very easy to get an A if you actually try. Just don't skip any of her assignments. Her conferences are actually pretty helpful.
Best English class I had.
Class for international students. Very friendly and understanding and willing to help. If you want to score good, dont miss class and keep up with the paper work!

Very terrible teacher? I don't know how she grades the paper, not a specific standard for evaluation, just depending on her life experience.  The conference of the paper is super useless, she will not point out the problems of your paper in conference. But grading the paper is very hard.

She is a really nice person, but she needs to lots of stupid assignments and does not really so corrections on the paper , it looks like she did not read it,and then she just gives a grade like that,if u take her be prepared to not take English lightly
Very good at her work.
Sweetest English teacher in ASU. Just pay some attention in class.
Requires work, but not an overwhelming amount. Overall, really enjoyed this class and got an A+.
She is very easy in grading and really sweet if you need help. Do make use of office hours.
Terrible professor. Rushes thru her assignments and blames it on us in the end. Does not know how to grade a paper if her life depended on it. Needs to go back to elementary school teaching.

She is very nice, but the problem is she is too quiet. She sometimes will tell us last minute work over BB with no warning, like assigning us a 7 page draft over TG break. She has a habit of getting behind on what we need to learn and her way of catching us up is making us rush thru our work. she is very easy, just make sure to pay attention A LOT

Terrible professor, but hilarious faculty member. He's rather off-putting be he complains a lot about the work you have to do for class; who want to use MATLAB when the professor himself admits to hating it? We did have a lot of running in-class jokes, though, which made class bearable.
Not helpful. Not consistent. Very Subjective.

He doesn't have any experience in MATLAB. Grading curve is extremely weird. He has a good knowledge of the content, but his teaching is much below the mark. His class is so boring that one would get a good nap in his lectures. Don't take it unless you are well acquainted with MATLAB or C.

Had him for Numerical Analysis.  Assignments were ambiguous.  Grading was subjective.  He told us in class full credit was 16/20.  Grader says full credit is 20/20.  He tells us class will be curved - it was not.  You never know where you stand in the class.  Plus he only tells you the general idea of how to code, not actually HOW to do it. HORRID

Seriously one of the most time consuming classes I've taken yet. His grading scale is ridiculous just like everyone else has been saying. If you don't look for extra work to do, the best grade you can get is a B. If at all possible, take a class with someone else.

In addition to the vague grading  (he doesn't have a consistent or publicly available scheme), where everything done correctly is 80%, he doesn't know MATLAB. The course is using MATLAB for numerical analysis. He comes to class unprepared and does nothing in the way of teaching programming. He tries to teach the numerical methods themselves.
What the other people say is true. Homework is very hard, weird curve and you begin with an 80 on every assignment and go from there. Very poor professor.

Weird grading curve where if you do everything he asks correctly, you get an 80, if you go above that with some vague unspecified and nitpicky 'above and beyond work,' you might get an A. Doesn't like being questioned, helpful in office hours but can make you feel like an idiot. Don't take if you can help it
Sam is a great teacher. Made learning fun and was enjoyable to attend class.
Sam was the man. Always super helpful and understanding. If you take WPC youll be lucky to get him as your professor!!
Great teacher! really helpful and easy to talk to. The class was great and I learned many useful things to help me be successful in WPC.
Nicest teacher ever, couldn't have asked for anyone better :) not bad to look at either. haha
Best teacher ever anybody taking WPC next semester or next year you gotta get this guy
Sam is awesome, best WPC 101 teacher there is! He always came to class prepared and stayed late if I needed help. Thank you!! :)
Awesome teacher.
Great teacher and every assignment was clear and helpful
Sam was very well organized and helpful. He will answer any questions you have on assignments immediately and he is very clear on expectations and requirements. Best teacher ever
the best teacher ever.
Great mentor for first year students and very easy going and understanding!
Sam was very helpful and answered any questions immediately. He is very well organized and he explains the requirements for projects very clearly. Best teacher ever
Amazing teacher, very helpful, responded to all my emails and ran the class very smoothly.

I loved this class!!  Keep in mind that this is a BASIC animation course.  It is great for students who are just learning about animation, or are interested in taking a fun art course.  Professor Garner is a great instructor.  He very kind and wants his students to succeed.  As long as you understand the basic concepts of animation, you'll pass.

The class was easy. Really easy. But the information was super basic, and it seemed really obvious that the professor had no plans and he didn't seem very enthusiastic. Weekly assignments were posted late andor cancelled. He wasn't always clear in what he expected. If you really want to learn a lot about animation, this class was kind of lame.

The class was not only a lot of fun but very informative. The textbook was used for some of the quizzes. You do not have to be an amazing artist to learn the beginning basics of animation. Mr. Garner made everyone feel artistic and creative. A great class to take from a great teacher.

He was nice and laid-back. First he would demonstrate the techniques and then going through it with us again. The class consisted of a midterm project and a final project only, but no grades were given until the final grade. He understood there was a learning curve though, so I still got an A by putting in the effort and showing I had improved.

He had the perfect personality for this course.  When you want to freak out on Maya, he kept calm and showed you what to do in a way that was easy to remember.  He had a dry sense of humor that worked with his straight forward teaching method.
Fleming is the man.

Easy class. Quiz every week and a few tests. Some of the quiz questions are used in the tests for that material.Must use book to understand material! As long as you take the time to find the answers, easy A for the class. No writing papers at all! Responds in a timely manner and very friendly. Would recommend!

Ellery was really great! The only downfall is that the time I took his class ASU wasn't really putting much effort into the 3D and VFX side of things in the film program. Would definitely recommend! Helped me learn and opened my eyes to the possibilities of working with VFX

I had Professor Connell for two separate classes and I enjoy and learned a lot in both. He has a backwards teaching style where most of the time in class you get to work on your projects and ask questions because he has already taken the liberty to create videos of all of his content. This makes for a nice, in class atmosphere.

If you care enough about film and put effort into what you do then it shows. He gives extra credit to the people that deserve it and is always willing to help out people who don't know something. He can be hard to learn from if you don't know a little about the subject matter already but you can always go to his office hours and Connell will help.

Great professor, I have taken 3 classes with him and meet with him on a weekly basis for help with a personal project! This professor has very good knowledge of the material he teaches and has videos for all of his lectures which is extremely useful if you can't make it to class or forgot how to do somthing! 10/10 and he grades very fairly!

Ellery is really knowledgeable about animation. I've been working with him on Unreal Engine and VR. He is really passionate and always interested in helping me learn more about the subject. He provides resources, especially online. He is always available when I have questions or need extra help. His technical skills are really impressive.
Outstanding professor--attentive, knowledgeable, and fair. Strongly recommended!

Connell is a great teacher! He really knows how to make use of media/technology which is pretty critical for animation he wants to teach you. He is also an artist and is quite passionate about the topic and you can really hear it in his lectures and teachings. HE ALSO GETS THE COLLEGE STUDENT LIFE, and is so chill on deadlines and giving time.

Super easy class. Showed up, watched videos, and discussed the editing techniques used in the videos via a discussion board. Assignments were easy as well, just 4 videos to make over a 4 month span. If you missed anything you can almost definitely make it up. Only cons are that he's slow to respond to emails and cancels class often.

He is an overall nice guy, but he was absent about six times out of the whole semester. He would email you an hour beforehand too with a bogus excuse. One time, he said that he sprained his ankle, but he came in two days later with no sprain. I just got my grades for my first project a week ago...14 weeks later. Easy A though!

He is really passionate about animation and you can really see that through his lectures. He was a really enjoyable professor and extremely nice. The only downside to his class is the way he teaches the software. We had to use After Effects for assignments but I became easily confused with the software and used Premier Pro instead.

I took him when he worked at the University of Wisconsin Stout.  When he left I got to experience several new professors who didn't even compare.  I never had a professor as enjoyable as Ellery.  He bonded so well with the students,  is incredibly intelligent when it comes to 3D modeling and knows how to get it across to students.

I personally liked this class a lot. The videos we watch are pretty interesting and fun topics. The projects are helpful because there are only a handful with helps not take up much time. And it also gives enough time to create some cool films. Doesn't teach much on editing, learn on the go really.

I wish he would have talked more about editing, I can't say I learned many new things. But his class was easy so no complaints... The TA was really helpful and Connell is helpful, but he takes a long time to respond to emails. The projects are easy and allow you to be creative and there are no tests, but discussion posts that count as attendance.

Most of the students knew more about what we were doing than she did. She didn't often know the labs she gave us, or get them, so it was up to the smarter people in class to figure things out. Could've been so much easier. But she was sweet, and it was easy to get an A I guess if you really pretend you care and have a good team.
Pretty sketchy, she is unclear and does not really know how to teach. Easy A class if you take her for FSE100 but if you have to take her thermo class, just don't
It wouldn't have been so bad if she actually knew and could teach thermo. Sadly I didn't learn all that much this semester. Avoid for the sake of your sanity, and integrity of knowledge

Among the worst classes I've ever taken. The idea behind it is cool, but the execution was horrible. You'll wanna scratch your eyes out after watching the same presentation every week. This class is group based, so you and your group will give 5 presentations total and you'll watch 25 others on top of the mind-numbing copypaste lecture from Duane.

This was a great class.  Very interesting.  It involves 4-person groups partnering with local entrepreneurs or small businesses.  The group consults for this person or business and, by the end of the class, creates an in-depth business plan.  Great real-world experience.

This class is not as bad as it sounds. Do not take if you struggle with math. Unlimited attempts on homeworks, 7 quizzes, 4 Saturday exams. Honestly, watch his lectures, take a few notes, and study the homework because he will sometimes re-use on the exam. He lets you bring a "cheat sheet" to exam and use excel.

This professor is better than a lot of people make him sound. If you do your homework and study for the tests you should be fine. He answers emails in a timely manner and is open to offering any extra help you need. I would definitely recommend watching the excel videos listed in the modules because these walk you through problems.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Test heavy

comment: Even though this math class is taken online I think he does an excellent job at breaking down concepts. You definitely have to work for your grade but the tests arent very hard. The class consists of 4 exams and 7 quizzes and theyre all done via Connect. I recommend him for ecn221!!

Fall 2019- He is an amazing professor who cares about his students' performance. Easy access by mail at all times and also has a good sense of humor. Yes 4 Saturday tests suck but they are easy if you CAREFULLY follow his videos and take proper notes. Go to his office hours and review sessions! Tip: Check your excel answers: mess with column widths
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Caring

comment: If math or stats aren't your favorite subjects, I don't recommend taking this class online, it is very hard to teach yourself. Your only grades are the quizzes and tests, and he drops the lowest quiz. If you decide to take this online, GO TO REVIEW SESSIONS every week if you want to do well on the tests and quizzes, then you should be fine.
Be prepared to read. If you read and follow the videos you will do great.

Beware of your decimals. I have the habit of rounding 3 places due to previous calculus classes and was marked down for not rounding 2 even though my math was still technically correct. The lectures lag and are hard to sit through. The tests aren't terrible, but I didn't feel the lectures/book prepped you well. Overall, make sure you prep for tests

He uses Adobe Connect for his lectures and they always lag. Also, he speaks kind of in a monotone voice and very slowly, so it takes a minute for him to get through his lectures. He is a pretty tough grader, but he lets you use a cheat sheet, so make sure you write everything down. Also, he tells you before exams what you need to know sometimes.

I booked my trip to Cabo in September and I took this class in my spring semester. After exam 1 i realized he scheduled the 2nd exam on the Saturday at the beginning of spring break. I explained to him I did not anticipated having exams on a Saturdays, especially not that Saturday. I tried work something out with him but he wasnt willing to help.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I have emailed him 3 times about a serious question and he still has not replied to me. I am going to have to drop the class because I can not get in contact with him.

I was worried about taking this class after seeing reviews but it is not that bad. Every week there his a hw, quiz and exam. The first two are open book. He created videos for you to show you exactly what is going to be on the exam and quizzes. Watch these videos and take notes and you will get an A.

Why is this online??!! If you struggle with math - like me - this will be a very hard class. You're graded by few things. Prof Molina's really nice though. If you ask him a question, he usually responds immediately and he gives you a cheat sheet to use for exams front & back. Still. Hard online class. People who suck at math, beware.

This is a tough class, plan to spend 3-4 hours per day studying. The professor tried to make things easier through examples on video, but often just made it more confusing. The exam and quiz answers page had mistakes or wasn't relevant to the exact question, makes it very difficult to learn. Grades were based on quizzed and exams only.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Your best bet is to learn how to get Data Analysis in Excel working, He demands its use, but never really covers how to use it. Did not learn from this guy one bit, if you had questions on material or lecture he would only point back to the material or lecture, and not answer the questions. McGraw Hill sucks and many problems are miss labeled.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Your best bet is learning from the book. Powerpoints, homework, even exams (yes, exams!) have typos and grammatical errors. Don't take unless you have to.
The professor is worst one that I have even taken. WON'T answer questions by email and so on. ONE THING to say: I will not take His any classes one more time.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Tests are tough--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Okay so Molina's class is by no means easy. But that isn't his fault, it's the content that is hard. If you take his class online, be ready for A LOT of work. If you want to get a good grade in the class you have to work for it. He has extra videos that do help a lot on Exams. STUDY. He answers emails very quickly and is clear about everything.

Wow. So I withdrew from the class about 4 weeks in because I seriously couldn't take it! I was anxious the entire time, I didn't understand any of the material, the video lectures were all via powerpoint & sometimes would be missing info on the screen. He has SO much due at the same time, on a Saturday at 9pm. Ugh, terrible class and too much work
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: I took Ignacio's online SOS325 session A class and was very disappointed. Although this wasn't a class I was particularly looking forward to, I typically do well and enjoy sustainability classes. I struggled with his grading because I could never tell what grade I would get. It felt like I studied, took the test, and then prayed that I would pass.

I took Molina and I will tell you now that his lectures are KEY to passing his course. He has lecture videos posted which he uses examples in that help you with the non graded hw. You only get graded on the weekly quizzes and 4 exams. You must do the hw to open access to the quizzes. Goodbye free time! This class took up most of my days.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: This is the worst professor at ASU. He gives wrong announcements, has a horrible grading system, relies solely on the book, and is not clear. ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Horrible teacher. When I ask questions, he automatically just refers to the book because he can't explain properly (even though I stated I already read the book). He doesn't understand that students asks questions because they don't understand the books. Grading is horrible, if you miss one question grade changes significantly. Worst professor ever

Took this online session A. 4 homework assignments, 4 quizzes, 4 tests. If you want his videos and copy the definitions from the book all of the work is easy. He was super responsive and answered my email questions promptly. Would take again

ECN 221 was tough to say the least. However, I don't think it is the fault of Ignacio. He does have a pretty strong accent and is difficult to understand but if you spend time on his lectures, read the chapters, and do the practice problems you will at least get a C. Also Exam 4 is SUPER easy! He uses only practice problems.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Ignacio is a horrendous professor. He doesn't explain any of the information clearly and often contradicts himself in  video lectures. The questions on tests and quizzes are often grammatically incorrect and unclear. If you to take Ignacio the class will be difficult, however, it is possible to pass. Ignacio should be teaching high school.

DO NOT TAKE THIS PROFESSOR UNLESS YOU ABSOLUTELY HAVE TO.  You take a 5 question quiz per week and your tests are only ten questions. So, don't miss a question or else you are already screwed. And those are your only grades! I am serious, take somebody else unless you absolutely have to take Molina. A 200 level class should not be this intense.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Only take if you're in engineering, business or have STRONG upper level math skills.  DO NOT take this class expecting an easy A. comment: I'm floored that ASU & WP Carey has allowed a mediocre professor like this teach such an important, critically required class. ratingTags: Tough Grader--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Ignacio is a graduate research assistantwhich is as low a rank possible for an instructor at a university. His background is not even in statistics. He was incapable of answering my questions. His was simply assigned to administer the class.  I am beyond disappointed in this professor and ASU, since this is my education and future on the line.

Ignacio was great, but the class is kind of tough if you haven't done econ in a while. Most of the answers are online, but some important ones you have  to figure out on your own (book helped somewhat, but I learned more from power points and lectures). 4 HWs, 4 Quizzes, and 4 Exams. He drops your lowest exam score between the first two exams.

Though it's obvious he knows what he is talking about, he has difficulties conveying it to students. He often asks questions in class that don't make sense, and when no one replies he assumes everyone is too shy. He takes weeks to put in grades and lectures are him repeating what was in the book, but taking much longer and making it more confusing.

Took this class online A session. What is on the exams is on the quizzes and homework. 4 homework, 4 quizzes, 4 exams, exams; definitions are word for word from your book, math is easy. I got 3 100's and a 97 on the exams and I am a terrible test taker. I ended up with an A in this class. He responded to my emails quickly and he was very helpful.

Very strong accent and will screw up in lectures and lead you down the wrong direction and will correct himself by saying "you know what i meant". His teaching style is slow and uninteresting. I struggled in this course and this is coming from a student who has taken two Econ classes before Professor Molinas course.

He is a nice guy but his teaching style is only good for people repeating the class. We had a review. He walked up to the board and wrote down the number of questions per chapter the test would be on. We asked him to help us with a few practice problems and he said no.

He really knows the information, but struggles to get the class to follow along. He does have a slight accent, but he is always willing to re-say it. Attendance is not mandatory, but it will hurt you if you do not go. During tests and quizzes in class, if he says ask questions...do it, he will guide you to the right answer!

He is a great professor! Really cares that you learn the subject and is completely easy to talk to. He tries to get to know the class which made the classroom environment so pleasant to be in. I highly recommend him if you want a more qualitative approach. (less math in his class compared to other SOS 325).

Professor Molina is an excellent instructor and does a really great job explaining the material. He is always willing to help and likes to talk with students to get to know them a bit more. Normally economics is a boring subject, but he made it relevant and easy to learn. Go to class, take notes, practice the problems, and study the concepts!

No help and grades unnecessarily harsh.  Practically everyone I talked to in the class was failing with a 30-50%.  Grades finally went up a little at the end, finished with a 70% and was the worst grade I had even though it's only one credit.  Stupid class.
Very harsh grader and she is not clear on what is needed for any of the assignments. If there is another professor for this course, select someone else.

Did not care for the class. She was not clear on assignment. She grades harshly and does not have any leniency. The concept was good just did not care for the teaching process. Chose another professor.

Loved her lectures and grew from class, but she is not a fair grader. I had perfect attendance and participated. Always says to dig deep. Its a one credit class-I thought I got something from it, but she still gave me a lousy grade. Give me a break.
She is horrible and doesn't explain anything to is and expects the work to be done.

Also took her for ASU 101. Cares "somewhat" about her students. Downside is, she does not give enough detail on assignments and just expects us to know everything we need to do without even the slightest clue. Makes it real difficult to pass such a elementary school class. A 1 point class should not have as many hw assignments as she assigns.
Unclear on expectations for assignments, unsympathetic grading considering her inability to explain her wants, never puts grades on Blackboard. Take someone else's class.

She is not very helpful I learned more from the students around me. She goes off on tangents and forgets about teaching I really wanted to take this class because I wanted to understand more issues people have both physical and mental. I would not recommend this teacher if you are actually interested in learning.
Easiest teacher. I know other people taking SPE 222 with different professors and it's much harder for them.

He gives you ample opportunities to edit papers.  You have 3 chances to turn in a paper in which he reviews it and hands it back before you get a grade.  Make sure you listen to his revisions! His class is composed of a few 1 page memo's and 2 research papers that are 10 pages in length.

He makes the class seem hard but its really not bad. There are a lot of writing assignments but he doesn't grade them till the last week of class. Awesome teacher and useful class. Hardly ever used the book and no tests.

hes just a dude who expects business students to act like business students. seems dry but if you ask him for help he will always give it and even comments that you are smart for getting your moneys worth. PS borrow a friends book but for the love of God dont waste money on buying one, we covered maybe 4 chapters out of 20
Adds many assignments that are unnecessary. He assigns a lengthy 10+ page group report as well as a 10+ page individual report. He also lacks any qualities that would make class enjoyable.
Extremely dull and dry, lacks any type of personality. Relies heavily on use of the text book to teach. Never even applies himself to help students learn. He is just going through the motions.
Super easy class. All of the assignments are due at the end of the semester, He's a really cool guy and super helpful if you contact his via email or go to office hours. I received an A.
Really nice guy! class is all group writing assignments. Actually enjoyed his class, and didnt think it was hard at all. got an A
Was easy until I saw my final grade. Completely surprised me. Dont take him unless you want to be screwed over.

Avoid this teacher!! He's super nice and you think this class is going to be until he's assigns a paper that makes no sense.  You never know what your grade in the class is, "everyone has an A, just turn in your final drafts"...so cool you never know what you're final grade is till after these not a chance to improve.
You have three papers to write and he's very clear with his instructions. He's always there to help so there's no doubt you will finish the course with a passing grade.

Helpful throughout all stages of writing your essays. Your grade is based on three essays and a reflective essay at the end, but you never really get a way to gauge how you're doing: he doesn't post grades on Blackboard EVER and essays aren't passed back until the next one is due. You will need a book because he assigns readings from it.

Sidey is a great professor! Taking his ENG 101 class was nowhere near the useless dread I imagined it would be. Your grade might be determined primarily by 3 essays, but his clarity and assistance are second to none. He stresses use of the book, but generally gives you sections to look over and nothing more. Take his 101, you'll enjoy it!

Useless class. Interesting topic, but he can't convey his ideas and connect them. Mid term was "straight from the class material," but the average score was 51%. Final was take home, and has nothing to do with the class material and they expect information from the readings. Not a very good professor.
Zhang laoshi is an excellent professor who cares a lot about her students. She's very helpful and supportive. I would definitely take another class with her and would recommend her to anyone.

Zhang Laoshi is very sweet and great at teaching! She is patient when it comes to you learning the language and well organized in her lessons. Attendance is mandatory, so make sure you show up everyday to class because you can easily fall behind.

A very energetic TA/Professor, she is extremely helpful and understanding of various levels of skill. She is very lenient with tests and quizzes but makes sure you learn a lot in class. I highly recommend her class to anyone interested in Chinese.

This is the best professor I've ever had.  He is the very picture of a dream professor.  Extremely kind and considerate.  Professor Ridge goes out of his way to help students.  He is very clear and concise in his class' lectures and feedback.  He gives plenty of opportunities to do well in his class.  Professors should learn from his example.

If you are a heritage speaker or have a solid grasp on Spanish grammar already, take this online because it will be extremely easy and it is a self-paced course. If you don't have a solid grasp on Spanish, it would be a difficult course to take online.

Patrick has by far been one of my favorite professors. He knows how to keep you engaged; helps that he is a looker! He's very helpful as he gives you study guides for tests. He is always open to questions & is down to earth! He replies to your emails quickly which is amazing! You have to obviously read, otherwise you won't do well. Sometimes tough.
Amazing teacher. The class content was difficult but the professor is extremely helpful.

Extremely helpful and always there to answer questions. Asks that you always speak Spanish to him (even in emails), which helps a ton! Makes the classroom a fun environment and everyone ended up being friends at the end of the semester. Doesn't hurt that he isn't bad on the eyes, either!

I've always done well in Spanish class until this one--class is really interesting and fun but Patrick is a very hard grader. I got a C on a test I felt really confident on, and a C on a paper that was everything he asked for. If you're looking for an easy A, he's not the teacher for you, but he's an excellent teacher and a great guy!

Patrick is great at teaching the material, but his grading is much too harsh. As a student who put in the work and has always done well in previous Spanish classes, I suggest not taking him if you want an A

Patrick is a great teacher. He doesn't speak too quickly and it's easy to understand him. He's always willing to help and responds to emails very quickly. He's young and fun and he's easy to laugh and get along with--everyone really respects him. His 325 class is pretty tough, but if you work hard and ask for help you'll do fine!

He was an awesome teacher and was very helpful. The class is upper division so it is getting a little bit more difficult but he was willing to help all the time and made it fun. Not to mention he is really hot.

Professor Ridge was great! He was always willing to help and made the class really clear. He was great about answering emails and was really helpful during office hours as well. I recommend taking a spanish class with him!

Extremely chill guy and always helpful. I would literally get a response from him sometimes within an hour! If you do the work you will get an A. Humorous and laid back teacher.He makes spanish interesting to learn. Would recommend him for SPA at ASU.
Super cool guy and was always willing to help

Patrick is awesome. Explains things clearly and helps if you need it. Speaks in spanish mostly but if you need clarification he'll speak in english. Nice guy. He doesn't design the class. The homework was all online, super easy. Tests aren't bad.
Great teacher with lots of enthusiasm! Really helpful with resumes and cover letters. Overall gives you a good sense and understanding of the W.P. Carey School of Business.

Dr. Thomas is a very sharp professor. Expect to read at least 3 books during this course. The assignments require a lot of writing and critical thinking. The quizzes are tough but filling out the study guide will help you a ton. There is a chance for extra credit if you read a 4th book and complete a writing assignment. You get what you earn.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: She is very tough. You need to read all the material and critically think. Sometimes I scratched my head at some of the grades I got on papers and such, but she is fair and isn't afraid to explain why you received the grade you did. This is NOT a walk in the park.

She is a very good professor. Her lectures are very knowledgable and you learn alot. The class requires you to read a few books and do short papers on them and there is a quiz every Friday. I recommend this class however it will not be an easy A. If you attend class and do the readings you will be fine

Great instructor and lots of fun! She is extremely intelligent and knows the material very well! Makes her classes lots of fun! However, she does not put them on blackboard so attendance is mandatory if you want to get a good grade! We had five required books to buy for the class. LOTS of work is expected and she is strict on deadlines.

She is an amazing teacher. She is very quick to respond to questions and give feedback on papers. She gives meaningful but polite comments on papers that help your writing and don't demean you in any way.
Fantastic teacher! She is very helpful and replies quickly to any questions. The class is very straight forward. There's a couple journal entries and three big papers (5-7 pages)

Over the semester there are 3 essays and for each essay you have to write an outline and rough draft that your classmates leave comments on (and you have to leave comments on theirs as well) which I wasn't a big fan of. Besides that Professor Russum is very helpful and the class is not very difficult.
Awesome teacher, never failed helping me in class, great sense of humor, grades fairly depending on how much effort you put in it, she is really helpful.
Great teacher. Very fun interesting teacher who knows how to have good discussions. The only bad thing about her is she is too hot. She is so hot that it can be distracting

Excellent professor. Expectations are clear, grading is fair, class was always interesting and it was easy to get a hold of her if you had any questions. She had a Pop Culture focus in ENG 101, which made the class much more interesting. I took the class in the hybrid format, and she used Schoology instead of Blackboard to manage the class.

It was ASU 101 so it was very easy. He was mostly gone on business trips but for the days he was in class, he seemed like a very good professor. He is a very clear lecturer and I would defiantly take any classes from him. Overall he is a very approachable professor for questions. He seems like he can teach any subject and teach it well.

Professor Shin is a decent instructor and is quite knowledgeable about the subject. Keep in mind that this course focuses more on the history/theory of popular culture rather than K-Pop itself. Also, there will be a short weekly DB post, 3 easy reading quizzes, a short reading presentation, and a final project. Class will mainly be for discussions.

Loves the subject and knows her stuff but really disorganized. Grades have not been posted since the first month of class so nobody knows what their grades are. Her grading criteria is not very helpful or posted too late and she doesn't know how to handle a class. It wasn't a hard course, but being confused all the time was kind of stressful.

Its the end of the semester and she has not posted grades for anything. No one in the class knows their class standing. She has even emailed the class saying she would multiple times and never did. She also doesn't know how to lecture. She knows the subject really well well cannot hold the class' attention. She also doesn't follow her syllabus.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: This is my 2nd class with Professor Shin! She is very enthusiastic about each piece we read. If you take this class don't be afraid to speak up in the group discussions. She loves to hear our opinions about the stories and what we thought about them. She is an amazing Professor who really cares about her students!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Amazing lectures

comment: I have taken both her KOR347 class and KOR321 this semester and I have enjoyed both classes with Professor Shin. She is very enthusiastic when she lectures which makes the class great. She has a lot of knowledge about films & she provided us with some interesting articles pertaining to the films. Her tests are pretty straightforward and it will be
One of the greatest teachers I have had so far. She is very enthusiastic about Korean films and she goes over anything that you didn't understand about your readings. Just an AWESOME professor.

This professor is nice, but I'm not sure if she has much teacher training. She knows her films, and selects some very good ones, but when it comes to handling the classroom she seems to be at a loss. She does encourage students to assert their own ideas but gives little feedback. This is a good elective class though, it just needs some improvement.

She is really laid back and strait forward. There is one group project, which you can choose your partners and 2 papers. The work load is medium. The only con that I had for this class was a few choices in films.

Kim ssn is an awesome teacher. He's very helpful in class and in his office during the hours that he's there. In class, he's also cheerful and pretty funny. He is full Korean, so his English sounds funny sometimes, but overall he teaches clearly and with good energy. One of the best teachers I've had in college.

Very dry lectures.  Some knowledge of Java is required prior to taking this class as you just jump right into everything.  Exams always had a somewhat poor average (ranging from 50% - 65%) indicating that something was wrong, but no action was ever taken on it.  Overall, unless if you're a Computer Science major, I would not recommend her.

Andreea is an enthusiastic, awesome teacher. Yes, this is one of the harder CSE 110 sections. However, you get a better understanding of the material and it help a lot in CSE 205. The later assignments can't be done the night of. Spend a couple hours the day of the test studying and you can easily get an A. Extremely helpful during office hours too

Requires some self teaching, but the homework projects are doable. The class was VERY easy if you actually paid attention and spent the necessary hours on projects. Otherwise of course its gonna be hard.

She is a Grad student who should not be teaching.  The first exam had an average of high F low D and she won't curve the grade.  For the homework assignments I needed help from my brother in law and even with 15 years programming experience he struggled on a couple of them.     The lectures are not helpful at all.
This class is harder than all other 110 classes. She is also not very good at teaching in general. Try to avoid her. If you get unlucky and get her, prepare for some tough homework and exams.
The easiest class ever. He's really nice and an easy grader.  I honestly don't know if he took attendance or not.
Tomas is an amazing professor, he is willing to help if you need something to be done. Answer emails back fast, he is passionate about Hispanic culture. I would take his class again!!!

One of the worst classes I've taken. He did no teaching - instead we read the textbook in class and watched random youtube videos. On "conversation days" he simply told us to "discuss a subject" with out partners while he played on his phone in the back.  Easiest A+ ever - but not worth the textbook money ($200+) or the time.

Incredibly unclear course expectations may scare you, but show up, turn in homework, and talk every once in a while and it is an easy A. Native spanish speaker from Mexico, he is helpful and likes to see you work in pairsgroups. Sit next to someone smart.

Hes very open to help and explain the topics. He likes to explain You Tube Videos in Spanish and related to the book assignments. He love the Spanish Literature and is always willing to talk about it in class. Hes inspirational and I am thinking on study abroad because of his recommendations. If he teach abroad, I will go for sure.

Tomas has virtually no control over the class. There's no structure, no clear purpose for assignments, and time spent in class is wasted watching YouTube videos (that aren't in Spanish). If anything, I would say that my spanish has gotten worse since taking this class because I am never challenged or expected to participate. Don't take this class.
If you plan on actually learning something, I wouldn't recommend this professor. His class is very unorganized and participation is far from mandatory. In other words, easiest A ever.

Lots of reading and some discussion in class. Medium level of note taking.  YouTube videos were used to enhance our knowledge. The instructor also gave input of history relating to author and how story relates to latin history. Very very interesting stuff !
This rating has been removed as per our site guidelines.

She makes the class too hard. Tests and quizzes are done on paper, even though it's writing Java and with Java you will always have a computer. She goes too fast with lectures. I recommend skipping the 2 lectures after a recent quiz/test and simply studying the notes online as well as the textbook. Assignments are too advanced for this course also.

I came into the course having little knowledge of computers or programming. I found Erin's teaching excellent. You need to remember to practice coding to fully understand the concepts. She drops the lowest exam, quiz, assignment, and lab. She also allows a sheet of notes during each exam. I'd recommend her to anyone.
She really wasn't that good of a teacher, very unclear and no makeups for tests/quizzes.

This is a really hard class if youve never taken programming classes before. shes always talking about how its dif. from c++ as if all the students took it before. She does go over code and examples. Team quizes to help make up ur grade. and a few extra credit points at the end of exams.
Erin is a great teacher, she is great at explaining code and giving examples. Very fair grader, and gives Extra Credit on tests. I highly recommend

ASU 101 is an easy class, enough said. You'll get an A as long as you pay attention and do the simple weekly homework. There's a presentation due at the end of the semester but it's pretty easy. Lectures can be boring but there's some interesting points.

Mike is an incredible lab TA. Not only does he go above and beyond to get us through all the experiments, but he was very willing to help out during office hours and by appointment. His feedback on assignments and lab reports is very helpful as well. He is incredibly knowledgeable, and an all around great guy. Highly recommend.

I had a great time in lab thanks to this TA. He clearly explained every lab before it started on the chalkboard, and his feedback on reports was very helpful. This man knows his ochem like none other.

This man is brilliant and extremely helpful.  Best Lab TA I have had and probably will ever have.  Provides appropriate feedback and even gives helpful lab tips to help you become a better chemist. He is incredibly knowledgeable about Organic Chemistry and will make you successful.  This man is a LEGEND.

This professor (and class) were phenomenal. The class is engaging and active.  Not only did I love the class, but this professor is just an absolute incredible person and teacher. The criteria here suck though.  It wasn't easy because nothing worth doing is ever super easy and my interest now is a 5, which really says it all!
Awesome professor! Classes worth taking. Information is enjoyable to learn and looked forward to classes
amazing professor and cares about her students so much!! great talks and first hand experiences.

Worth the effort and the hour plus commute. you would be surprised as to how many people SHOW UP for this class--she is passionate about the course. Tests are fair. drops the lowe4st score. study the voc words--they are tested on the final!  One of those professors that made sure you applied it to everyday stuff. Prof Sanford was fantastic!!
it was not an easy course, but worth it. Would recommend this professor for this course. She has practical knowlege that was useful in this field and lectures great!
Take her! She was great. Very clear and inspiring. Would take any course she offers. best professor at ASU!
Class hard to get into but worth effort.   reading required-- lectures entertaining. Not an "easy A". Take her outlines, study guide. Go to the "weekend gatherings.
TAKE Prof Sanford for LES 305!! Not an easy class. TAKE HER !!!

This class was better than I'd anticipated.  If you take it online, you're allowed to use your notes and textbook for the exams.  I was shocked when I got 100% on the final...:)  But that aside, Dr. Sanford is very informative and an excellent professor.  A heads up though for the online class:  you will need a webcam for the proctoring program.
ratingTags: Respected--Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria

comment: Sanford IS THE BEST!!! Her classes fill up quickly. The commute to West campus is definitely worth it. ASU is lucky to have her --we have a celebrity! It is entertainment at its best! The topics are hard, but she does a great job of explianing. TAKE HER CLASS!

TAKE THIS PROFESSOR!!!! If you need this course--must take it with Sanford. Best professor I took.  She is inspirational and engaging.  Material is not easy, but Sanford does a GREAT job of spoonfeeding. Would not recommend taking it with anyone else. She meets Saturday mornings for extra tutoring---two to three hours!!!

Loved the class! I wasn't really into the legal aspects, but the book covers a lot and the quizzes/exams are open note/open book. I utilized the glossary for exams studied for the exams. The radio videos are long but the other lectures are interesting. If you're taking this class, TAKE THIS PROFESSOR!!!!
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Inspirational--Clear grading criteria

comment: The best professor you could have.  She knows what she is talking about and takes the time and effort to explain the material.  I took the in person class and it was worth every minute.  The book might make the material look boring and hard to understand but Sanford describes the material extremely well.

Took the online class and A was practically guaranteed. You don't need to look at the weekly videos, just the review slides and your book. As mentioned by others, almost everything is open-book so tests/quizzes are no sweat. Very low time commitment.
Absolutely engaging. Strongly recommend.
Best professor at ASU. She is AWESOME. Not an easy class, but worth the effort and the time. Takes time to explain and offers tutoring on Saturdays
Excellent! Really enjoyed the course. Saturday gatherings are great--two hours of tutoring by the prof. Exams are multiplechoice and  quizzes are true false. Memorize the outlines!
GREAT CLASS! Strongly recommend
Prof really cares about students. Spends saturdays tutoring those who need extra help. Awesome class!

Great course! Recommend taking this class if you are interested in global business. Prof Sanford knows so much. ASU is lucky to have her! Quizzes are easy, but exams are difficult. Read the book and use the outlines she provides.

Enjoyed this course. Definitely would take professor again. She is conscientious and has high standards. lectures are easy to understand. Well-structured format. Ethical awarensss has  short essay. Exams are Open book.

Online quizzes are open book, but require you to do the reading. Outlines she provides are really good. She has a lot of credibility. in depth information on international issues and news-This was a useful class!
Probably most useful course I have taken at ASU. Its a lot f work, but worth it. Professor Sanford is awesome!

Super! Really enjoyed this class. Prof Sanford's lectures are well organized. She provides detailed outline with help with exams.  Snapshot the charts she writes on the board. They are helpful!!  Sanford is caring and takes time to explain difficult concepts. Highly recommend her class

This was a great class. It is clearly an upper division course so don't expect spoonfeeding. Professor Sanford is the real deal. Google her! Exams are curved and lowest exam grade is dropped. Quizzes have two attemopts. She is approachable and friendly. Saturday morning tutoring was helpful. i would take any class she teaches.

Dr. Sanford obviously cares and tries really hard to help her students. She is probably the nicest teacher I've ever had. However, she is extremely unorganized, ill-prepared for each class, doesn't know her slideshows at all, and lectures on good information, yet irrelevant to weekly chapters. So much reading and self-teaching; so little time!
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Besides for her own published book that was needed sporadically throughout the course (mainly for the ethical awareness assessment), I enjoyed her class and the resources she provided us with. It was a great course to learn about general & business law. RPNow was annoying but regardless, her class will work if you put in time outside of a classroom
ratingTags: Get ready to read--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria

comment: For the online class, all the assignments but one are open-book and open-note. Everything you need is in the book. Get familiar with the book, have it on hand, and know how to find the answers in it while taking the timed weekly quizzes and exams. It's not a hard class, but you have to do the work. And have the book--it's a free A if you do.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Clear grading criteria--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: I thought this class was made harder than it should have been.  TOO much reading involved for a 300 level course, sometimes 2 chapters a week, plus weekly quizzes,  required links (at least few a week, 2 hrs or longer), reading from her published book.
Really enjoyed the class. Lectures were entertaining. Prof uses practical examples. Strongly recommend hybrid course.

Quizzes and tests all open note, open book with all questions and answers word for word. Only hard assignment is the ethical awareness assessment, but she curves EVERYTHING. Two tries on each quiz, one due every week. Videos and audio lectures useless, just use the slides and textbook.

Really enjoyed this class!  Hard to get into, but definitely worth the effort. Class fill up quickly. Every lecture had fascinating material. Great to have someone of her professional stature. She provides sound reasoning and requires students to think critically about problems and consequences. BB outline andaudio recordings  are very helpful.

AWESOME! Very inspirational. really enjoyed this class. Saturday morning gatherings are great. Not mandatory. very useful. Exams are multple choice. Quizzes are true false. Sanford has empathy which is her greatest quality. She is compassionate and understands some bad stuff can happen

Outstanding teacher. always answered all my questions. she's a great career mentor and provided us with meaningful feedback Outside of the classroom. She is considered the go-to person for many students. Class gives practical information about the law and real wrold expamples
Hybrid class is definitely worth the trip!

Great class and great teacher! She develops a good rapport with students. Sanfordis one of the most caring professors I have had at ASU. She is passionate about teaching and spends extra time with students. Exams are fair. Quizes have two attempts.

Take her. Sanford is BEST professor I had at ASU. The lessons I learned in her course about ethics and international business extended well beyond the textbook. She is passionate about empowering students. Her Saturday morning gatherings really helped me with online class. Sanford really dedicated to her students.
Good online class. Straightforward study materials. Open book exams and quizzes except for one quiz.  Repeats much of what is learned in other governmental or business classes.

I enjoyed the course.  Sanford was easy to contact and reasonable with due dates (such as extending assignments due the weekend following thanksgiving). 4 weekly quizzes, 2 exams, and a final. Tests are open-note but timed, administer through proctor U. Overall a great course.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria--TEST HEAVY

comment: Taking this class online. The quizzes every week were easy, but the tests are harder then they seem. The tests are only on a few chapters at a time, so some chapters you only read for the quizzes & not the tests. Material can be repetitive from government and business classes. Instructor doesn't factor much into online class unless you go to office
Tests can be studied for by using the powerpoint. She curves everything so you can get an A with a decent amount of effort. Not a cake walk, it s a law and ethics class

She didn't always respond to my emails. Ethical Assessment was hard. The Ethics book was extremely hard to read, full of vague legalese. Cheeseman book was great though. Course was great, challenging though.
Lots of quizzes and exams but all but one are open note/open book. I recommend the online book for easy searching.

There is no extra credit like someone else suggested. She does curve exams but half of them were curved because she told us to study the wrong material. She teaches over 400 LES students so if you actually think anyone is going to watch you take an exam for 90 minutes, think again lol. Pretty easy class though.

This class is pretty difficult if you don't treat it as important as your in-person classes. Do the quizzes and always try to get 10/10 (option to retake each exam once for the higher of the two grades).  Every point matters in this class! All except one exam are open book/notes so take advantage of that an get an online version so you can search

Lots of reading for weekly quizes. Three tests and she drops one and theirs cum. final but it dosent cover everything. Curves when class does not do well and offers extra credit on tests. If you read the chapters a once or twice you should do well on tests. Quizzes are pretty easy too.

She is truly an amazing person. read her bio!! or google her, she is the real deal and I respected that!! I almost wish there was more work graded to give you incentive to keep up. she gives tons of reading and you must read every chapter but theres like 4 quizzes 3 tests and that's it. so no hw everyday is nice but you better read for those tests

Really straight forward online class. Do the quizzes every week. You can open the quiz and have enough time to search for the answers in the book as you take it. Have to use lockdown/webcam testing though, so no internet help. The big assignment in the mid semester is graded tougher and the sources are more ambiguous than hoped for.

Really enjoyed the online course and learned so much. Would definitely take another class with Dr Sanford. One of the hardest classes I have taken while at ASU, but definitely worth it. Not an easy "A" but you have tow attempts for quiz and lowest exam score is dropped.

You can get an A or a B easy. You have 2 chances for the quizzes so just go back to the first quiz, write down all the answers and then take the 2nd quiz again, although there are a few new questions. Her actual ability to teach an online course is horrible. She literally does not even know what her OWN exams are going to be about. Total joke.

Class is mandatory for my degree, so I'm a bit biased. I feel that Dr. Sanford is a bit egotistical. I love the real world examples, but there is waaaaaaaay to much 'me me me' content. Would've liked to see more external opinions. Very wordy, lots of reading for weekly quizzes. Perfect course if you're a good test taker and hate busy work.
She is a wonderful professor. I like her so much. Her class is interesting and she's always willing to help students. If I have a chance, I'll take her class again!

She is a fair teacher who is engaging and inspiring in the classroom. She's very knowledgable and cares about her students. If you take her class always check that the points you've "earned" are correctly entered in at the end because even though I contacted her, I got no email back and lost the A I deserved due to a math error.

Awesome professor.  Do your readings and you will pass the class.  All quizzes/tests are open book/open note and she drops your lowest test score.  The textbook is actually an interesting read as well.

Really enjoyed this class! Quizzes and exams are challenging, but they are open book, open note, and exam grades are curved. Your lowest exam grade is also dropped. Dr. Sanford is very organized, and her Blackboard page is easy to navigate. Responds to emails quickly! The class is simple but challenginghow school should be. Highly recommended.

TAKE THIS CLASS! She is there for students and goes the extra mile ---even gives her cell number. Her lectures are entertaining and informational. My favorite ASU professor.  In-depth knowledge on many current topics, particularly data protection reform and international white collar activities. Material  is useful. Exams curved. Drops lowest score
Excellent material and made it very interesting!

She is truly passionate and enthusiastic about teaching. She does not hesitate to stay after class to discuss topics more in depth and takes calls on her personal cell phone. I would recommend you take her in person. The classes are fun and enjoyable. She gives clarity and focus to real world issues and encourages you to trust your instincts.

She truly is amazing professor who clearly you can tell loves what she does for a living. This class is not easy, and is not meant to be. Be prepared to do a lot of reading it is a Law class so duhhh it is expected. Read chapters before attending class because she goes of that. It is lecturing class to lecture what you should already know.

Dr. Sanford is an amazing professor! I totally loved her lectures, very motivational. She is very helpful and is one of the professors who actually likes her students and wants them to succeed in the real world. Just as long as you go to class and read the book you you will have an A. She keeps in touch even after the semester is over. The best!

Professor Sanford is amazing! She really cares for the students and wants you to be successful! Her class is great for discussion so do the reading. Very helpful and relevant topics as to what is happening in the world today and the challenges that come with ethical decision making. Not everything is black and white.
She is awesome!  I would take as many classes as possible with her she also teaches LES305! She knowledge is extensive and you will truly learn a lot in her class!

I got to know Dr. Sanford more than most of my in-class professors. Two years after graduating I got in touch and she helped me through the entire law school application process and has been crucial to me getting into my dream school. She is so dedicated to her students!! If you care about the course she will help you through it and more!

Her expertise is incredible! We learned real world topics that matter in business like:  cyber security, money laundering, corporate corruption, terrorist financing, data protection reform, and counterfeiting. She helps students in any way possible academic or professional. AMAZING WOMAN and Professor and Mentor!!!

Dr. Sanford is a phenomenal professor!Not only does she have a wealth of knowledge in her field but she is also understanding and is willing to go that extra mile for her students. There is a lot of reading in the class but Sanford explains the material in lecture and makes sure that you are prepared for the test. Definitely take her!

Dr. Sanford's course was extremely interesting, useful, and it gave you an in-depth look at important topics like cyber security, counterfeiting, corruption, and money laundering, which we can encounter in our daily lives. Dr. Sanford truly cares about her students & helping them to succeed in and out of the classroom. I would highly recommend her.

An excellent lecturer, it's inspiring to hear her personal story in regards to ethical business issues that are current and relevant. You won't feel like you are learning about a case from 15 years ago, but will get information that can be used right away.

Take this course online if you can! Quizzes are very easy, all the answers can be googled. Tests are lockdown browser, but open booknote, which makes it less of a burden to study for. Drops 1 of 3 regular exams, not including final, which are not overly difficult by any means. Relatively easy course, online at least. Get the book for exams!

Attend all the lectures and you'll do great, she speaks about fairly interesting topics. Exams are generally curved and she gives extra credit on exams to the students who go to each lecture. Weekly quizzes, 4 exams (one drop) and a project assignment where you watchlisten to videos and write paragraphs on each. Book is ultimately unnecessary.

I had Dr. Sanford for the hybrid class in Spring 2014. Did quizzes online and exams in person. Exams were very hard. She rushed me, while she was explaining the material, during the office visit. If you like legal (boring!) stuff and learning precise definitions, you'll enjoy the class. Had it as session B, was such a big struggle.

If you have to take this class through ASU, the online version is a great option. Open book, open note tests and not a bad workload. Some material is pretty dry but the ethical awareness stuff is pretty interesting and you can tell she's passionate about it. An A is very possible.

Really great class. Learned a lot. She actually taught me the information. She is engaging which is rare in an online class.. Dr Sanford is nice  and helpful. She gives out her cell phone number so we can call her if we help or  the computer freezes

Class lectures are very interesting - which made it easy to attend class. There is not a lot assignments for points, so you have to make everything count.  She is a very well respected teacher though and I would take her again.

Dr. Sanford is one of the best instructors. Class is extremely interesting, it relates so much to the business world, especially business law. Was hesitant about taking this course but I'm glad I did with Dr. Sanford.
Great class.  I also took MGT 302 from her. Definitely recommend taking BOTH from her. Materials are great and she tutors during office hours.

Ms. Sanford failed to post any test scores before the withdrawal deadline so I had absolutely no measure of success leading up to that point.
