I emailed her asking if she could tell me my score because it was very important that I find out what to expect in her class. She responded with "you get to drop one test"... No help at all. Had to withdraw:(

This was a fantastic learning experience!I was pleasantly surprised at how much I was able to learn from this class. I think I took my education to a whole new level. Dr. Sanford is a great teacher- everything is well explained in her multimedia reviews and lectures. I took MGT 302 with her too. I only wish she taught more subjects

This was the most entertaining class I took at ASU. Dr. Sanford asks for feedback and listens. The exams are essay and multiple choice.  The essay are all are covered in the weekly lectures. Final exam is comprehensive, my advice---keep up with the material to pass the final--it is not an easy class, but if you study you do well.

I really liked this class.  no need to get the book, cause Dr. Sanford has over a hunderd slides for each chapter. Her powerpoints have audio and go over most of the book. Exams are hard if you dont study the slides, but you can drop your lowest score. I highly recommend taking her class. There are tons of study tools.

The material was not all that easy, but there was plenty of study help to get me thru it. Actually, this class had the most study stuff that I have seen since starting college. Pretty cool class, I just hope I use it in the real world... I studied hard to get that A! Communication with her staff was rough, but she always stepped in to help out.
very easy class. took the class online, didn't use a book as it was all online powerpoints. learn the terminology and thats all the tests were.

Pretty easy class, don't really need the text because the online powerpoint reviews posted explain everything you need to know for the exam. The exams are straightforward often worded alot like the text and then have an essay portion. Not a bad prof but I found her assistant to be more helpful
Do the work and study the material and you will do fine.
This class was a hot mess to say the least. There were constant MindTap problems ($145) and they took forever to get back to you on issues. Save your time and money and choose a better teacher.

I did all 7 extra credits (though it was time consuming)and got an A+. Printed and made flash cards from MindTap which helped me a lot. Each exam has 2 essay questions, so you need to read the textbook. Final exam was conceptual and covered all chapters. Some materials overlap with MGT300 & SCM300. MindTap costs $180, doesn't come w/ actual book.

I like this professor, but whatever you do, DON'T CHEAT! she has a reputation for catching cheaters. I didn't have to, I read the book & watched the lrctures like instructed and did ok. Exams are face to face so I didnt have to deal with vproctor. She has lots of multimedia stuff, listened to it in the car. Really helped. I defintely recommend!

Class was difficult to say the least. The online class uses surveillance so be aware of what you do during the tests!  It could come back to bite you in the butt. I would recommend taking this class in person.  Hard to understand her during the instructional videos.  I found her to be very informational, but nothing excites me about her.

If looking for an EASY "A"--- do not take. This class requires understanding the material. To do: weekly HW assignments (one wk to complete); 4 quizzes (two attempts); extra credit; three exam(best 2 out of 3); comprehensive final exam. You can't get by just studying vocab words, b/c of the FINAL EXAM. Need to keep up.  GOOD CLASS!!

Cool class. Learned alot of interesting stuff in a short amount of time. Workload manageable as long as you keep up with HW & learn the material, exams are not hard, final is comprehensive but if you have been reading and watching mutlimedia videos you should learn enuf to get an A. Glad I listened to her announcements. She is very helpful. A+

I wish other classes I need to take were taught by Dr. Sanford.She makes it easy to understand the material. She is clear and uses good examples. Met with me an goes beyond to help ANYONE who asks. Even if you don't have an interest in this subject, take her.

I want to recommend this great professor to you. Extremely nice and helpful. You gotta listen to her chapter review sessions to do well on the exams. She knows her subject and can answer just about any question you might have.
Great class! Dr. Sanford is one of the best professors I have had. She is so knowledgeable and willing to give extra help. She treats students like people, not numbers. I learned so much from her!!

Was dreading this class, but turns out its really interesting. Dr. Sanford has a co-professor in this class. Chris generally handles the tech issues. If you can make it thru all the stupid MindTap issues, this is actually a good class. Lots of information and study tools. The exams aren't too hard if you use all the multi-media tools. Good stuff.

Great class. multimedia reviews on each chapter are very helpful--Dr. Sanford is knowledgeable and great at explianing. Extra credit points available.  HW assignments and quizzes. Not bad---one week to complete. Before taking this class I was worried about taking MGT 302, I would definitely recommend her class!! ENJOY!

This class is interesting. Videos on different countries and multi-media sessions with lots of interesting info. Dr. Sanford makes it easy to understand hard concepts with lots of real life examples. She gives a week to complete HW assignments. Textbook is not boring--I definitely recommend this class over others for graduation credit!!

TAKE THIS CLASS!!! Dr Stanford is GREAT! Videos, powerpoints, tapes, flahcards and more. Dr. Clark is also very helpful.  They make a great team! I would recommend this class even if you do not need it to graduate

I did not do as well as I would have liked. The course material is educational and I will use it in my future career. I think it would be better as a 15 week class--the accelerated class requires the same amount of reading.  Dr. Sanford is excellent. She is willing to answer student posted questions with flushed out answers.Her reviews are helpful!

TAKE THIS CLASS!! This is a great class. Dr. Sanford provides online review sessions for students to refer back to at a later date, tests are logical and review videos entertaining!  I especially liked the discussion posts. She is very knowledgeable and has a great voice! I would definitley take another course with her.

ASU is lucky to have her as a resource. Dr. Sanford possesses impressive level of knowledge on the material. She took critical thinking to an entirely new place. She was very understanding of technical problems and responded quickly to emails. Resources she has are endless.  Her Review sessions are extremely helpful.
Great online class!  Strongly recommend.  Great professor!!!

I didn't find this class that bad at all. She was always willing to help. Quiz every week, but it was rushed since it was an expedited course. Two chances per quiz and 5 discussion boards are so easy. (Couple Sentences) Made us retake a test and choose the higher grade. You're watched with a webcam on tests now. All online and her voice is great.

By far the worst class I have taken at ASU.  She does not bother to teach and its impossible to get help from her.  Her tests are compromised of questions that aren't even full sentences. The only thing that is useful are the flash cards which come from the book's website.  The vproctor was terrible and would delete paragraphs of my essay on tests.

Great class! Straight forward professor, no suprises. For a dry course the professors materials are entertaining, helped to digest textbook, & the work is doable. One bad thing, tech support for this class was horrific, wish I could have taken this class in person. Exams were glitchy with vproctor, but she grades exams on a curve, so I survived.

Best online class I've taken, even as an accelerated course! Fair grader and the essays are interesting. Not crazy about the multiple choice exams, but I never do well on those. Good news is if you tank a quiz, she lets you retake it. She taught in a way I can understand. I liked the reviews and videos, really helped. She also listens and cares.

Not an easy class but she's a very cool professor. SHe met with me anytime I needed and gave lots of exam review help. If you take this class, reading is everything. Was weird being watched by Hal 2000 during exams though, but you get used to it. I liked the scenarios and learning about myself and how I wuold act in ethical situations. Good class,

She is a nice professorand and want students to learn as much as possible.  the essay questions If you are not good writer and don't know how to write nonsense thing, and fast typing skill,you will get stucked essays. The final exam count 35% even if you get 100% before if you fail on final you fail every thing.

Do not take her and this online course offered by her. You will be monitored by video surveillance while take the testS. There is no clear guideline for grading the essay parts of the exam. She is impossible to set up a meeting (I tried a few times). You will want to kill yourself after a couple weeks in. I almost did. PLEASE SAVE YOURSELF!!!!!!!!!

I really enjoyed this class. I usually don't like online classes, but I felt she was always there and a real live person at the other end of the computer. This class was entertaining and you will learn ALOT. She has tons of knowledge and it shows. The discussion board made it easier for me understand th material and confirm I was right! SHe is cool

All the Multi-media review sessions made this course worthwhile, definitely one of the best online courses I have taken. She really obviously cares about her students, always goes the extra mile. This is not a boring class and I got stuff from this class that will help me in my future. Really opened my eyes to things I have to be careful of.

Online half semester class: THERE ARE SO MANY BLACKBOARD ANNOUNCEMENTS (about 3 a day). Ten discussion board posts and a quiz required every week. There's an exam just about every other week. The work isn't *hard* but it is tedious and largely useless. Enjoy!

I took this class online I definitely recommend getting the book and doing the readings. One quiz/week which you get two tries on each, and an exam every few weeks. Exams use the lockdown browser so you need another computer if you want to try to look stuff up- lots of the questions are online, part multiple choice, part essay-timed- so be prepared

Teacher does not clarify, hard grader, lots of reading, assignments are time consuming, test are  difficult, teacher does not respond to emails,  I would  recommend this course with a different teacher.

lots of reading, lots of writing. firm due dates. as of time of writing the class is in session and not yet completed. thought this would be an easy blow off class but its not. expect to spend time on this class. interesting teacher, but that only goes so far when your neck deep in an essay.
This was an easy mandatory class.  The professor made it interesting and bearable throughout the semester.

Hands down my favorite teacher I have had so far at ASU. She is young, quirky and engaging. If I could take her class for english 102, I would sign up in a heartbeat. If you have the opportunity to sign up for her class, do it.
The class mainly focused on three writing assignments, all of which were pretty easy. She grades fairly easily and as long as you show up and put in effort it is a really easy class.

Professor Hyde is a very quirky and fun teacher! She gives very useful feedback and is always willing to give more help if you need it. There are multiple extra credit opportunities, so take her up on them. As long as you go to class and do your work, you're guaranteed a good grade!

Allegra Hyde: Is quite possibly the greatest English teacher of all time, funny, clear in what she wants, engaging. She will help you in writing a better paper if you just ask for help. She also tries to get you in the habit of using the writing center for help (Extra Credit) and I thank her for that, will use in future english's.  - Drew
Really helpful professor. She'll push you at times, but my writing improved a lot. Also she's fun. Definitely recommended.
Wonderful professor, very enthusiastic, smart, knows and loves the subject. Highly recommend!

Very helpful and cares about you grade. She sets up one on one meetings before each major writing project is due and you only go for 15 mins, its very helpful. She is super sweet and is always open to new ideas. Easy class !

Very easy class, there should be no reason to get an A. Ms. Hyde is a very easy grader and doesn't require too much and is really understanding to the college student lifestyle.  Classes can sometimes be a bit boring and awkward as she herself is somewhat awkward but overall enjoyable. Recommend her if you want an easy A with relative ease.

She is really quirky, but very nice. Kind of untraditional so she likes to sit in a circle and have discussions rather than legit lectures. Really easy grader. Just show up to class, do the assignments, and it's not hard to get an A.
Easy if you just do the work.

One of the best teachers I've ever had. He made rocket propulsion feel as easy as a high school course while still being very thorough in his lectures. He provides tons of supplementary materials outside of notes and homework to tie in real, more detailed examples. Makes you feel one step closer to being a real engineer.

He knows how to teach. He is funny at times and serious when needed. Study notes, exams are lengthy but couse was graded relatively. Class is very sorted. Develops interest in the course. Best teaching style I have ever seen.

BEST BEST BEST professor at ASU. He is literally building you to be an engineer. He teaches really tough classes, However, he makes it the easiest. Propulsion is known to be one of the hardest classes in aerospace engineering. However, he made it an easy A class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--TEST HEAVY

comment: Dr. Dahm is by far the BEST professor I have ever had and will probably ever have. He cares massively about his students and is EXTREMELY knowledgeable. He encourages you to think/understand the material rather than just recite it out from memory. You will actually learn about what he teaches you and truly obtain something from his classes.

By far the best professor I have ever had in my life. Amazing lectures. Trust me you don't want to miss them. His notes are very detailed and very easy to understand. If you refer his notes, you won't need a textbook. Take him.

He is 'The best teacher' I have seen in my entire undergrad and grad experience. I have been taught by some of the best in the world, I kid you not, but Prof. Dahm's  competence in all aspects of teaching, including subject knowledge & teaching ability is unparalleled.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Amazing lectures

comment: I am in his turbulence class right now, and he kinda is the best teacher I have ever had. Even though the class is really hard for a beginner,  he does give very clear lectures. Homework is heavy and difficult, but helpful to understand the content.
The single best professor you will ever take, hands down, end of story. Take this class. Do it. Do it now.   If you pay close attention, he makes subtle, dirty jokes in lecture.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Hilarious

comment: Excellent professor, by far. Dr. Dahm is enthusiastic, clear, and helpful. Homework is very useful, but his lectures are sometimes math-heavy and go by fast. His exams are long, and you'll probably get poor scores, but don't despair! For perspective, 69 overall is an A+. Phenomenal experience, you won't be disappointed.

Possible one of the best teachers I ever had. He clearly knows and cares a ton about the material. Homework actually really helps learn the material and he publishes his own solutions with the homework so you're never stuck on a problem you can't figure out. Just an overall phenomenal teacher.

This is, by far, the clearest professor I have ever had. His English is perfect, understandable, and he has a witty comment or joke here or there. What the others say is true, its like he developed the content himself. You feel like you're learning WITH him rather than just being talked to. Highly recommend, if you fail, it's only your fault.
The quality of teaching you would expect from MIT. Among the best professors I have had at ASU. Feels like he discovered the material himself it's so clear.
Best professor at ASU.  Extremely helpful.  More interested in you learning than grades

One of the best professors I've ever had. He is extremely clear and concise and lectures tend to flow seamlessly into both the homework and exams. Pay close attention in class and the exams will challenge you but you will feel confident you did well.

He expects a lot, but is reasonable.  Always do your homework on time as he is extremely strict about exact deadlines (he will count down the seconds).  He is extremely clear about what he wants you to understand.  He knows his stuff.
I HATED THAT CLASS! SHE IS RUDE, RUDE, PLUS RUDE!

Start the writing projects early on. She will even look over them for you if you ask her after class. For the quizzes - use the CD inside the book. The quizzes are VERY similar (in some cases identical) to the ones in the book.

His lectures are great, but it's evident that the student's participation in class matters a great deal, do not go on your phones or have side conversations - his pet peeve. An inspirational speaker, great to learn from.

Easily one of, if not the best educator I've ever had! His lectures are so effective, I didn't even realize I was learning. If you miss a few classes you'll still be good, but please try to go! He's truly an amazing professor.

Lance is a fantastic professor and keeps the class engaged at all times! Really nice as well! The only thing I did not like about him is it's very hard to get in contact with him via email. He seemed to never respond so if someone needed his help in a timely manner it wouldn't occur. Overall, he was great!!
I really liked Gharavi from day one, hes charismatic, funny, and brilliant! You get homework monthly, you take a midterm and a final exam and that is it. Easy A.

Dr. Gharavi is a fun guy to have class with! A lot of his lectures are done by guests, which are interesting. There are about 5 100 point assignments + your midterm and final. Attendance is taken via writing your name on a notecard at the end of each class, so show up. The textbook isn't necessary, but read it if you genuinely care about the topic.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Hilarious--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: This professor is really understanding and if you show up and do the work, you will pass with no problem.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures

comment: Lots of class discussions, too many boring guest lectures. Attendance taken at the end of class, very funny lectures by the professor himself. Very few assignments and all are very easy. Both the midterm and final are easy multiple choice exams that only require you to learn the vocabulary used in class.

He's very engaging. Funny and ecstatic about the subject material. Really easy class. Only a few short writing assignments and short quizzes about the reading material at the end of class. Don't think those count for anything though. "Mandatory" attendance. Grades writing assignments pretty leniently. Easy A.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Hilarious--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Professor Gharavi is hilarious and really good at keeping the class engaging. The content is fascinating and I would strongly recommend him to any arts student.

Easiest class I have ever taken, by far. The only homework is writing a short story every once in awhile. There are mini attendance quizzes each class, however those are not graded and do not count for anything. Gharavi seems like a nice guy, but you only really watch him lecture a couple times, there are mostly guest speakers.
Lance is amazing and comical! Please take his class- you won't regret it! He is extremely passionate about the arts and he's been nominated for funniest professor! That says something!

I really want to take Prof. Gharavi again! He is such an out of this world kind of guy which makes his class super interesting and fun. The lectures were cool and actually taught you things. Plus he includes puppies in his powerpoints.

There are a few assignments and a quiz every class period on the reading, but they don't count for much of your grade so don't worry about those. Just come to class and do the assignments and you should be good to go.
Fun class, worth attending each class.

Professor Gharavi is quite the character and this is a very entertaining class! It is a must have for most theater or film majors, but do not dread it: He will keep you on the edges of your seats. There is about one assignment per month, and attendance quizzes each day. Pay attention and you'll ace the midtermfinal without studying.

Dr. Gharavi is by far my favorite professor. His lectures are hilarious, and the only time I was ever bored in his class was when we had a guest lecturer. Would DEFINITELY take his class over and over again.

Gharavi is an amazing teacher! So passionate and excited about what he teaches. I really enjoyed the class even though I am not in the arts field. Writing assignments were fun, we did have a two question quiz every class for attendance purposes (super easy). I definitely recommend his class!
Gharavi is passionate about his work and gives energetic lectures. This was my favourite class this semester and he was my fave prof. Pretty much a fun class,thought provoking, 10/10 would recommend.

I honestly thought this class wasn't that interesting. But with that said, a lot of people enjoyed it - Gharavi is quite the character, which is amusing. Go to class. That, and studying the study guides for the mid-term & final will help you SO much. Show up to the lectures, take notes, and study a little - you should pass with an A/B, no problem.

Greatest professor you could ever ask for, he is so entertaining and funny, I only ever got bored during a few of the guest lectures. I always enjoyed going to his class. If you have the chance to take a class with him, TAKE IT!

Do not take notes in the class, just listen. He is so crazy and brilliant it's entertaining. I liked his guest lecturers. He made you aware of other classes which include stories. One of the very few classes I looked forward too.

I love Gharavi! He is literally a genius. He has inspired me so much. The only downside to the class is that there are a lot of guest lecturers who are often times boring, but when Gharavi is teaching it is fascinating.

This man is wonderful! and is definitely a theatric. He makes every class enjoyable and the students add to the entertainment. Keep in mind, however, his work is serious. Doing the assigned readings is recommended in order to be successful in his quizzes. I personally learned a lot in his class, Intro to Storytelling, and will miss it!

Always looked forward to class! Amanda's lectures are always interesting, and you can apply everything from class to your own life. She is such a sweet woman, and understands that a class called "Stress Management" shouldn't add more stress to your life. Easy work in class, but definitely learned something everyday!

Amanda is the best professor I've had yet! This class is highly interesting and she gets research to back up every point that is made or question that is asked. Living life in a mindful way has changed my life. There is so much to learn from Amanda. I only wish she taught a higher level class of mindfulness so I can learn even more!!

Amanda is really sweet. She is a very empathetic individual. Her class taught me invaluable life lessons and has already improved my quality of life. This class is very easy to get an A+ in. There is a fair amount of work to do, but it is not difficult by any means. I repeat, Amanda is super sweet and I highly recommend her.

Amanda put a smile on my face every time I walked into class:) She is awesome! I definitely learned a lot of beneficial techniques for sustaining a better and more happy life. Work in this class is very simple! Do it and you'll receive an A for sure. If she had another class I would definitely take it! Very passionate!! and cute!

Professor Watts was new to teaching this class when I took it. Although there were some confusing moments at times he was such a nice and helpful professor. He does not want his students to fail so he will curve or adjust test questions. Review his lecture slides numerous times and you will be fine.

Interesting class. Tests are just like the study guides. Open book tests and the final is a grade replacement. Seriously, don't be a punk and never show up to the class. It's not that boring. May as well go. Good teacher, decent class.

There's a big project with a real company. Fun, but not revolutionary. What are his qualifications to teach Adv? He tells you how he was a multi-sport athlete (him?)and created machines for $1. Here's what he is, he's a textbook & PowerPoint lecturer with a lot of frills that's going to trick most students into thinking he's an expert. He isn't.

Dude is the BEST Professor I have had at ASU so far. Really knows his stuff and keeps the attention of the class really well. Chapter Quizzes are easy and if you do the Study Guides for the Exams they are Easy as well. Really laid back and overall a great professor. Highly recommend taking his class

Albert is the best professor I have ever had. Made class interesting. Very involved with students and extremely CLEAR and fair on tests. do the study guide and its the test LITERALLY. TAKE HIS COURSE!!!!

David is one of the most genuine professors and he truly cares about the students. He wants all of his students to succeed and do well. His class is extremely hard if you don't attend class. I love Albert, he is the best professor I've ever had.

Albert is the man. He really wants you to learn and succeed in the course. He is very helpful with everything and his project is very resourceful and similar to the real world. Overall, if you want to learn more about advertising, take this class, you will not regret it!
BEST PROFESSOR I HAVE EVER HAD!!! LOVE LOVE LOVE HIM!! Easy to get an A and fun!

Class was not mandatory, but I always looked forward to going. Sage is a very passionate and  astute individual. She makes the lectures fun and interesting even on the topics that would be hard to do that. I definitely recommend taking her class.

Prof Sage is an amazing professor who seeks the overall well-being of her students. I've never had a teacher more inclined to reach out and help her students! Fun, caring, and energetic to name a few. Great hair too!

Professor Sage is extremely helpful. Anytime you email her she responds kindly and is always willing to help her students. Easy to tell she truly wants her students to learn and succeed. Definitely suggest taking her.

Professor Sage is AMAZING! It's easy to tell that she is an extremely intelligent individual and truly cares about her students. She responds to emails rapidly and is always willing to help. TAKE HER!!!

I really enjoyed Professor Sage's class. She makes tax VERY interesting and you can tell she is passionate about the subject. The subject is a little tricky and can get hard if you don't read the text outside of class, however she is very fair with grading and only wants her students to succeed. I highly recommend her! Great professor!
Wonderful Teacher. The material can be challenging but as long as you commit yourself to it, you can get through it. Email her with any questions you may have and don't procrastinate!
Took tax law with her. I got a 100% and spent maybe 5 hours total on the class. Did require some work, but it was sort of interesting and it is an easy A.

Responds to emails and questions any where between 6-8 days. Gives very vague feedback. Does not respond in time with adequate suggestions for improvement on future assignments. Behind in grading for over half of the 8 week session.

With Kendra as a teacher, this class will be an incredibly stress free one. Just make sure you do your assignments! She is extremely helpful and incredibly understanding. She knows that being a college student can be pretty intense, so she provides a little wiggle room. If you do not get an A in her class, it's on you.

With Kendra as a teacher, this class will be an incredinly stress free one. Just make sure you do your assignments! She is extremely helpful and incredibly understanding. She knows that being a college student can be pretty intense, so she provides a little wiggle room. If you do not get an A in her class, it's on you.

Super nice lady! She accepts late work. Says attendance is mandatory but it wasn't even though she had us sign in. Just a few assignments and no tests. All of her ppts are online and the assignments were no brainers. I really suggest taking her she will definitely boost your gpa

The service-learning aspect of this class was amazing. You gained real-world experience and were able to make connections within your industry if you chose your internship wisely. The lectures were interesting and provocative. My only criticism is that she did not grade in a timely manner nor did she give feedback on work.

This class was super easy. All you had to do was get your service hours done and complete your reflections on time and you got an A. She saved all her grading till the end of the semester and gave me the same grade on every reflection, so I'm pretty sure she just entered in an average which kept me from getting an A+ but oh well.

Veronica is really nice and made the class interesting! The best part about this class is the internship, and if class wasn't mandatory I probably wouldn't have attended. Writing assignments and quiz weekly, but they are pretty easy just time consuming.
Veronica is a great teacher who is invested in seeing her students succeed. She is funny and laid back, and is overall just awesome.
She really motivated me to become more actively engaged and think about the implications of my actions.
Spencer is very helpful and actually wants to help his students do well on assignments. A tad bit awkward during the lectures, but a great professor overall.

Spencer is a good teacher. He gave full credit just for turning in weekly poems, and he did his best to engage students during workshops where the whole class was supposed to contribute. Unfortunately, poetry is a difficult subject for people to catch on to, but he did his best without being overbearing or unfair. Highly recommend!
Over all a very fair grader and a good professor. I highly recommend.
Fair grader and provided straightforward assignments. Grade is based on participation and 3 essays over the course of the semester. Overall very good and fair professor, I would highly recommend.

The only issue with this teacher was that he seemed very uncomfortable during lectures, enough that he sometimes seemed to give up on the lecture entirely. Other than that I really liked his writing advice and insight into the lessons.

Did a good job for her first time teaching this class. Sometimes test questions were a little confusing but as long as you read the book (which has very short chapters) it is a very easy A. Would take a class with her again!

This is her first year teaching, so I think she was a little unprepared. She is a very sweet woman and generally cares about your success. She is a push over about grades and gave a lot of extra credit. The downside is her test are not worded well and are confusing. I mean 18% of people got a T/F question right lol
This is the lab for MAT 343.  She is an excellent TA, and is extremely helpful.  Go to her in her office hours if you have difficulty in the lab.  I could not ask for a better lab TA.

Great teacher and is very knowledgable. He is strict with grading and will make you work for the A. I still gave him a 5 because he really was a great professor, I learned a lot and had a great time in his class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Clear grading criteria

comment: I had Patrick for both the online and recitation portion of COM259. He goes beyond expected to provide feedback for his students and create lecture materials. The type of professor that loves to speak with his students and set them up for success. Online quizzes are super easy and the midterm directly relates to the course content.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Patrick is a lot of fun and very approachable. Class is based on one semester long group project so your group can make or break your class. A good amount of out of class work but not that much busy work. The quizzes are only from the textbook so you have to read it. Really enjoyed and made a lot of friends would recommend.

Very nice teacher who is always willing to help and teaches great. However, his grading is very tough and it is not easy making up missed points at all. There is a lot of outside the class work as well so prepare for a lot of group meetings and projects.

Super nice and genuinely caring professor. Will look over papers and tell you exactly what he wants in advance. Very clear guidelines. Lots of group projects inside and out of class. Tests are online and come straight out of the textbook. A few extra credit opportunities are offered throughout the semester. If you do the work, you'll pass

Take Patrick! he's super cool and funny. His lecture's are not boring at all and most of the assignments are group projects and quizzes. He doesn't give homework other than the quizzes and evaluations but it's really easy, you can use the book for the quizzes since they're online and the evaluations are minimum 400 words.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Group projects--Amazing lectures

comment: GREAT TEACHER!! He is very funny and keeps you engaged in class. The curriculum is very group centric so you could get unlucky with a bas group, but otherwise, easy A.

He was a great professor and he made class interesting. We had an issue with one of our group members and he was very helpful and understanding. There is not a lot of homework and the exams were pretty easy.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Take Professor McDonald! There are several assignments but they aren't hard at all! He is the best COM professor! His midterm is a little tough and he counts for attendance. Just show up and do your work and you'll get a good grade!
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Way much harder for a lower division class. Final grade highly depend on the groups assign in. Unlucky, bad groups and tough grader(barely any extra pts) make this class a nightmare for me. I worked so hard get my groups together and actually work on our stuff but still useless. Hugh amount of pts deducted by group paper. upsets me so bad
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: TAKE THIS CLASS IT IS INCREDIBLY EASY AND FUN SOMETIMES
Pretty easy class, quizzes and discussion boards and then one final project that you complete assignments for every other week.  Clear expectations and responds to questions very quickly.
Such a great prof! Makes lectures interesting and engaging. Easy quizzes each week, short essays, and a few tests. Solid amount of group work, but extremely manageable. Take McDonald!!
this class is very difficult. you should do many things, and he is very strict to the essay, it means you may lose many points. The quiz is easy.

Must complete volunteer work to complete class that is done with a group that is assigned. Quizzes were easy if you skim the chapters and the tests were not that difficult. A little extra credit given.

Prof McDonald assigns five reflection and he also has the standard BB quizzes that are pretty easy. He had a group project that was pretty dumb. He gave us very open ended direction so it was hard to figure out what exactly he wanted. This wasnt a terrible class, but it wasnt a good class. Out of all of my classes this was my least favorite.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: I enjoyed his class. He gives clear expectations and was available when needed. Encouraged and required group projects. Easy to follow what was required. Clear deadlines.

If you're looking for the best Communications professor, then take a class with Patrick. This guy is amazing, fun, energetic and loves to teach. He made waking up twice a week for a 9am so worth it. Although the work was a bit tough, if you do well on the exams you'll pass. Go to class! He is amazing and my favorite teacher from my career at ASU.

Professor McDonald is very energetic in the morning as well as a great teacher. McDonald has to be one of my favorite professors. The class is based off of groups throughout the semester which I think is great. I enjoyed the class and how he ran it.

The class was great, he followed the syllabus to the very end, so read the syllabus, do the homework and everything is self explanatory. The group revolves around one huge group project which is easy, and it just takes a lot of time to get everything organized. The only thing that sucks is that I got a B+ and was one point away from getting an A-

Patrick is a good professor that relies too much on his TAs for grading. In this class, his TA would regularly take points off of assignments without explanation or even rubric categorization. When contacted, she was curt and then unresponsive. It's really too bad, it could have been a great class without the petty, arbitrary and opaque grading.

McDonald is a must have professor. He is hilarious, fun loving, and so knowledgable. I love working with him, he really cares about his students. You will learn so much applicable things in his class. Yes you will have to read if you expect to pass, but it's always interesting. TAKE HIS CLASS.

This is the second time I have taken a class with this professor. He is one of the best professors that I have had while at ASU. He is well educated about his topics and knows what he is talking about. The tests are not that hard if you go to class and think outside the box.

I got him for com 230 my first semester of my first year of college and then purposely took COM 250 my second semester with him again! He's very lenient, easy grader, and makes all his classes super fun due to his sense of humor and stories from his daily life! I loved going to his class so much that I got mad when he cancelled any of them!

Majority of grade is based on group projectsposts. Seemed nit picky with writing assignments (4 Individual Papers, 1 Group Project). Encourages us to use Google+ for communication, and then did not answer all posts in class group. Overall was extremely friendly. Do the work and do what you can to make your group work and you will get an A.
He is not understanding. Very difficult. Went to every class, did all the homework, and went to office hours and still did awful in the class. If you want to pass, take someone else.
Patrick is very funny and understanding and I loved every minute of the class. His lectures were interesting and I think he is one of the best teachers I have ever had.

One of the best teachers I have ever had since Kinder.  He is very funny and is always there to answer any questions regarding classhomework. I highly recommend him to anyone who is looking for a great Communications teacher
Always happy to help. Huge Star Wars fan. Lots of fun excerises but a large chunk of work needs to be done outside of class. Attendance counts for grade.

This was an interesting class, the only part that was not as good, was the team projects. There are always those who try to skate by, and do not assist. Overall, if you want to learn more about communication in a group setting, this class is a good choice, and the instructor does provide good feedback, however not good feedback on your papers- ASK

Good professor who makes things clear and is very helpful. Class isn't too difficult but there are a lot of pieces that go along with each speech that need to be followed closely. Overall, a good professor

HILARIOUS GUY. Such a great professor and super cool!! Pay attention to your notes and book as they will be of use in class especially when it comes to exams.He is a harsh grader, I might warn you, however he is entertaining. You will work with random group members so good luck with that.Expect a few 30 minute presentations, so dress to impress!!

Patrick was an AWESOME teacher, I looked forward to going to his class every week! He's funny, easy going, understanding, and teaches the material in easy to understanding way that everyone can relate to! TAKE HIS CLASSES!!!
Awesome teacher, he is funny and   very helpful. One of the best teachers I've had at ASU.

ONE OF MY MOST FAVORITE TEACHERS AT ASU!!! this class was pretty easy and quite enjoyable! he has a way of catching everyone's attention so we're all listening and engaged. Papers were easy, tests weren't too bad.  He made study guides that if you study, you'll do fine! I'm an average student and i thought this was an easy class!! :) RECOMMENDED

Boring lecture.  His TA's teach the friday section (smaller) and they grade papers.  Tests are open book and all online.  They're pretty easy, only 10 questions due Thursday night.  Final & Midterm taken in class.  Not super easy, but not terrible.
Boring lectures but a very easy class

Only thing that sucks about this class is that you must buy the textbook brand new from the bookstore and you can't sell it back. Other than that, this class is easy but may require a bit  more work than other classes. Make sure you always pay attention to the rubric, do your readings, never miss deadlines, and fill out the study guides.

The clicker points really add up so go to every class. As cliche as it sounds, this class is extremely easy if you just attend the class, read/skim the chapters for the quizzes and completely fill out the study guide for exams.

Reyes is a really incredible professor. You'll have to read, but you can go from complete lack of knowledge of what cells are part of the immune system to in-depth, up to date understanding and comfort reading papers published months ago and understanding how the findings impact the field. If you possibly can, definitely take it with Reyes.

Amazing professor. Is clear, enthusiastic and gives examples that really bring the topics to life and give them relevance. He values critical thinking over memorization  but for some things you just need both. Easily one of the top 3 of life sciences professors at ASU. After taking this class I immediately signed up for MIC420 whim - also amazing!

Fantastic teacher. His enthusiasm is contagious. He knows most students by name and I've seen him remember students who took one class with him and ask them about their lives. There are some mistakes in his slides and his accent can be hard but he will spell things on the board to make sure he is understood. His tests are challenging but inspiring.

Dr Reyes is a smart guy, no doubt, but his lectures are horrible. His accent isn't always easy to understand and he rambles. Learned nothing in lecture for month, stopped going, and relied EXCLUSIVELY on the Janeway's immuno textbook. TOUGH CLASS, Over Half of the students originally enrolled dropped. Learned a lot, but all through the text book.

Typical ASU professor: Cares only about his research, not his students. Grades attendance and assigns groups as if we were still in High School. Slides are full of careless mistakes and his lectures are confusing rants. I would have learned more if I had stayed home and read the book by myself! Luckily, you can get an A without learning anything.

Hands down best lecturer I have ever had, both here at ASU and at UCSD. He really tries to make class a conversation as opposed to just talking at you. Questions are welcomed and encouraged and he answers them thoughtfully. Immunology is a very difficult subject, mainly because the information is so foreign. I highly recommend this class with Reyes

I absolutely loved this class with Dr. Reyes! 4 multiple choice exams with an optional final. Tons of extra credit offered on exam and on online quizzes, which was great. I found that it was best to use a combination of studying lecture slides and supplemental reading from the textbook. Class requires effort, focus, and time but is well worth it!

He was a great professor. His tests weren't very bad. He was helpful and funny, he actually made lecture interesting. Instead of clicker points he had us do online quizzes. A lot of extra credit. I would definitely take another class with him.
He's really into infectious diseases and how movies in Hollywood portray mass pandemics.  Very interesting guy.  He has both a Ph D. and MD from Mexico.

Hands down worst prof. I have had. It's not his accent that makes him hard to understand but his complete lack of organization. He goes off topic and his tests are ridiculous. Not because they're very hard questions but because there will either be no good answer or 5 good answers. I would avoid taking this prof. if at all possible.

I don't know what everyone else is talking about: prof Reyes was easy to understand, to the point and helpful in his office hours. Not once did I receive a standard email from him: very personable! He obviously knows what he's talking about. I only wish the class would be smaller, and he hadn't been so nice to slackers in the course.
Can't understand a word he says, and doesn't focus on what is needed for the exam. talks about one thing in class and tests you on another.
Very enthusiastic lecturer, but his strong accent makes him very difficult to understand. Exams are difficult, and averages are in the 60's. No curves. I would not recommend this instructor.

Nice guy and very smart.  I think he could be a very good teacher, but I had problems with his accent at times and it was not always clear what was important to learn from his slides.  I will not take more classes from him if given the choice.

Professor Reyes is also an MD, which makes him an incredible source of knowledge. If you want a smart, knowledgeable professor who is also a very nice and fair man, he is it! The structure of the class focused on busy work and testing more than true learning though, which I found distracting, but he may have inherited the format from Dr. Nickerson.

I took the Gender, Sexualities, and Literacies online course as a first-year student; I was able to do well. The syllabus was very clear and Dr. Guzzetti gave detailed feedback on every assignment -- positive and constructive. Two papers a week based on readings in the textbook. Discussion boards supplemented learning. Time investment, but worth it
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--So many papers

comment: Not the best class but I did learn a lot. I found the text book online for free. Weird discrepancies in her syllabus and directions. Papers took me 45 minutes max each and there are 2 a week. Easy grader, rarely got points deducted. If you write at college level and understand APA citations I don't understand how people wouldn't all get A+s.

I definitely did not enjoy Guzzetti's teaching style. This class caused me so much stress this semester. The assignments are extremely tedious and repetitive. Her grading is extremely rigid and she deducts points for formatting. She will remove your assignments from Blackboard and make you re-do them if you make mistakes.

Guzzetti has students read her text that she wrote and cite from it on every paper. The class is called New Media, but her text is like 10 years old as are most sources she uses. In order for it to be new media, she needs to UPDATE! Not hard class tho.
ratingTags: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--SO MANY PAPERS--Clear grading criteria

comment: This class was advertised as a creative writing class, but it turns out to be screwing around on Second Life and then writing about various pointless materials within the syllabus. Be prepared to have half points taken away for not citing a textless, speechless video or two sentences that provide nothing in your papers. Truly ridiculous for 400 Lv.

I signed up for this class hoping it would be a unique experience--I deeply regret my decision. Guzzetti looks for ANY reason to deduct points from papers. Her grading is arbitrary and subjective. She cares so much about Second Life that it inhibits her ability to grade objectively. She's condescending in emails and unhelpful. HORRIBLE PROFESSOR.

Dr. Guzzetti is an excellent professor. Her directions for writing the papers is clear and concise and she gives great feedback regarding what you wrote. The material is complex, so be ready to spend the reading time thinking. Great class, loved Dr. Guzzetti!

One of the worst professors I have ever had in my school career. Her syllabus is a mess, she marks off points for unclear things not mentioned. She lists her book as optional and then forces you to answer questions on your paper that involve her book and then marks you off for "not reading the material". Lacks empathy towards her students. HORRIBLE

As a class, it's great. The professor would dock points for everything in our weekly papers. I would even receive points off for things not listed explicitly in the homework questions. I am an A student that understands the material, but this teacher will go out of her way to not give you 100%.
She is an awesome teacher. Just a lot of reading and there is a paper due each week. You can get an A if you stay focused.

I recently concluded a course with Professor Guzzetti, and it was honestly one of the worst courses I have taken in my academic career. She does not care about her students and disregards emails. I found her to be completely rude and lacking empathy. Also, she will most likely make you buy her textbook, which is terribly expensive and uninteresting
Great professor, hands on, papers every week are fairly simple if you do the readings. Amazing class for an online class.

Took Intro to New Media as an online summer course and loved it! I'm not going to lie, it was pretty easy but really interesting. We got to explore virtual worlds and other niche sites online. Would definitely recommend this professor if you like online courses!

Took Virtual Worlds Topic; awesome class! Dr. Guzzetti is very "hands on" for an online class & was there to help us with ANY questions we had. The work is easy but Dr. G really wants you to think about the subject we're studying. She responds very quickly & is eager to learn about the students as well. Would def. recommend this teacher!!

So far 2 week in he has wasted every class period. Talks to us about useless stuff and talks to us like we are 5 years old. I wish we could use the time to learn something like Mobile App Development. It would be nice to not have to waste my money to get my degree.

This guy is an amateur. He obviously has very little industry experience and is a career academic. I would be shocked if he remains in his current role moving forward. He is truly inept, and the applications he has developed and demos in class are embarrassing. Avoid this professor at all costs. Worst professor in the CIS major.

Dr. Dan is such a kind, helpful guy. He truly cares about the success of each of his students and goes above and beyond to help you with the material and prepare you for your career. Due dates on exams and major homework assignments could be spread out better, but I won't give him anything below a 5.0 because he really is a great professor.

Great professor who you can tell is very enthusiastic about the subject! One in-class lab, small homework, and quiz are dropped and one group project in place of the final (which was fun!). Professor Mazzola is very clear on how assignments are to be graded based on the rubrics he provides. Demonstrates something new every lecture as well!

Mazzola is a pretty good professor. A little bit old fashioned socially. Tailors his class and anecdotes to men. Teaches a LOT of helpful applicable material. Some HW is very tedious. The class is super passable and helpful but yo have to pay attention. Not too hard or time consuming overall, but definitely not easy.
Daniel Mazzola was an awesome teacher. He is one of the few professors I felt that really cared about each student, and he did everything he could to help you.

Phenomenal teacher, wants "something for you", and very understanding. He truly wants his students to succeed. I would strongly recommend him; in a sense, he has drastically changed my college career for the better.

He is the worst instructor that I've ever had. He is hostile and does not care about the students. In the beginning, he acts like he cares, but soon you will find out the total opposite. He doesn't understand the material that he teaches and hates it if you ask him questions.
One of the best professors I have taken at ASU, very strict on the set guidelines but he does know his stuff and teaches it well. He comes to the class well prepared with his material to teach.
He is very unreasonable and he criticizes some students' work for no reason at all.
The worst instructor ever. Don't expect to learn anything in this class. Unfortunately, he is the only one teaching this course.

Dr. Dan is a good guy and a good teacher. Expectations are clearly laid out in every assignment. He does a good job of presenting all of the class materials in an easily digestible manner without making it impossibly hard. Not a particularly hard class if you pick up SQL quickly; follow the rubric.
I can't wait until this class is over. He is the worst and never answers your questions. He is very rude too.
He makes the course very easy. Most students get A, but you really don't learn anything. It is a very boring class too.

If you show up and actually make an effort to complete each assignment, it should be an easy A. Dr. Dan will help you with almost any problem. He won't give you the answer, but will help you figure it out or research it yourself. Great teacher!

Dan is an awful instructor. He really doesn't understand the material himself. That's why he gets upset if you ask him questions.  His PhD is in Business Administration which has nothing to do with CIS. His dumb jokes are not funny at all and he is very rude.  His class is a total waste of time.

Dan is incredibly rude and does not help you outside of class at all. He constantly interrupts you if you ask questions. The material gets fairly difficult toward the end of the schedule. He hates it when you ask questions/ask for help.

I loved Dr. Dan's class. He's a pretty goofy guy but you can tell he really knows his stuff and cares about students succeeding. The material itself was pretty difficult but the exams were easy. There are group projects but try not to stress over them too much, they're graded pretty leniently. Overall, you'll learn the basics of networking

Funny guy, and pretty good professor overall!  The Ruby portion of this class was a little much, too advanced without any instruction.  Tests are relatively easy, and he genuinely wants you to succeed.  You'll have a few group assignmentsprojects, be ready to allocate time towards that.  He's always available to answer questions and help!

Awesome guy, and definitely a cut above the rest when it comes to the people in the CIS department. Very enthusiastic and energetic guy, and you get some good insights into networks. The Ruby component of the class was light, but its nice to get a little exposure. Knows his stuff when it comes to IT career development!
Great Teacher. Enthusiastic about the subject and often uses real world examples. One of the best professors I've had at ASU.
Awesome Teacher!!!! Cares about Students Success

Unix class with no book. The first half of the semester is all about the korn shell and the last half is about writing programs in unix. Prof is very caring and will help in any way he can but won't give you the answers. He is also a very fair grader. There is a midterm exam that he helps you with and the final is a group project to write a script.

Great professor with real world experience and enthusiasm for the subject, not to mention very caring about student success. Though he only uses PowerPoints, he makes the material interesting and applicable to the real world. Assignments are almost too easy and I wish there was more Ruby, but a great class overall.

Easy class, but learned a lot. Quizzes and Tests are all fill in the blank and matching. There are also a few Ruby coding assignments that help you learn how to learn Ruby. Overall I learned a lot and enjoyed going to class.

Patterson is passionate about Biology, and a funny, nice guy, but so incredibly boring. So hard to focus in lecture, and you're never sure what exactly you should be learning/taking notes on. His BB lecture notes are really helpful to study off of, but powerpoints are not. The class is teamed up with Elser, and pretty difficult.
Taylor Jaeger is seriously THE MAN! Give this guy a raise. He was my break-out instructor for ACC 231 and he was awesome. The guy knows his stuff and is down to earth. I would chill with Taylor Gang!
she doesn't grade very hard, but she's not very responsive to emails. Make sure you email her multiple times to ensure she gets something important.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: 1 of the 2 worst teachers I have ever had.  Constantly patronizing. Rude to students and does not respect our responses or questions. NEVER responds to emails which is not helpful especially when dates on the syllabus don't match up to what is posted online. Extremely bad at giving directions. If you ask a question, expect her not to answer it.
She is a very rude professor and made it very unpleasant to actually go to class.

Horrible teacher. She is awkward, and rude. Went to every class, did the random journals, and an hour long flow for the final. She didn't grade the midterm or final paper until the day grades were posted after classes had ended. She also somehow thinks a 92/100 is a C. Not fair grading and no response to emails. Would absolutely not recommend her.

The journals were super easy to do. They were only up for a small period of time with no reminders by e-mail or in class, which is fine if they were on a more regular schedule but they seemed to be randomly placed during the semester. Creating your own flow for the final was a bit ridiculous and awkward for the structure of the class, but doable.

Angel was apathetic toward students and rather awkward. The journal and written assignments were easy. The final isn't bad either, and overall an easy A if  you don't miss class. Unfortunately she tends to ignore the "and Pilates" part of the class title, but I learned a lot about yoga and it wasn't too bad of a class except for the 7:30 am part.

Instructor was great, she helps people that wasn't doing it correctly. Journals and also assignments. Plus a final that you have to put all exerciseposes together for a final. Overall great person and is there for you!!

Fun and easy class. We had to write journals and papers, which I was not expecting for a 2-credit hour dance class, but they aren't too hard. Directions can be confusing, but overall a pretty good class.

I did not enjoy this class at all because the exams were hard and I read the book. She is strict on not packing your things until time is up and also having side conversations. I personally disliked the way she taught but it wasn't the easiest "A" I could get at ASU.

Easy Humanities course. Everything is CLEARLY laid out in the syllabus. She makes a schedule for the course and follows it exactly. I highly recommend this course if you want an online course that is at your own pace and doesn't require a book. She doesn't reply to emails very quickly, but there should be no reason to email her, read the syllabus!
Easiest A at ASU. It's horrible, but I guessed on every assignment and test and got an A+. 100 extra credit points for attending an extra dance show.

I don't know what she is like in person, but for an online teacher, she was awful. No support, no guidance; her lectures were hardly professional and no real learning took place. For an "easy" online course she sure made it my least favorite of the semester.

This class was tough for only a 2 credit class, but very interesting if you are into yoga. Angel is nice, but the dance department rules are strict. For every class you skip after your first 2 your grade is dropped by 1/3 of a letter grade...OUCH. So don't take this class unless you are committed. Besides that, the assignments and grading are easy.
Professor Jimenez is fantastic.  He answered any questions and was always available. He was very fair and provided quality feedback. I would highly recommend him.

The class is straight forward. You have two compositions the consist of a rough and final draft. 3 written and 2 oral exams. The prof. doesn't really speak english well but I think he grades easier because of it. He is very flexible and patient.  Do all the hw and come prepared for the weekly chats and you will at least get a B, If got an A.

For ECN312 he only teaches Theorems and Proofs of those theorems. Thats all every class is. He just stands at the bored and walks you through the derivation of random equations but never explains how to use those equations or even gives examples. The only grades are 3 tests and a final, so you never get practice. DO NOT TAKE HIM!!
ratingTags: TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: For most students this may be their first difficult economics course and I would say having a decent math background is necessary to understand the material. Read portions of Naive Set Theory by Paul Halmos. I could have done better in the course, but okay given the effort I gave. Textbook helps and he skips over proofs of most theorems and lemmas.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: If you like math and logic, you will really enjoy this class. If not, you will probably have a hard time. But he is responsive to people's needs and doesn't mind explaining things over and over again. What's the most important is to be proactive.

Because of him, I totally hate Economics. He doesn't care whether you understand or not. He is unwilling to teach and wouldn't give you help as a standard professor. He isn't behaving as an adult. You would probably see a kid dancing in front of you and showing his intelligence.

Please do not contact or talk to this "genius". Do not take his class unless you are smarter than Alien. Bad logical map, worst handwriting. Nothing is clear from his mouth and his dance. A wonderful researcher, the worst Professor. He really though he is  the next Narsh.

Class was tough, but rewarding. If you struggled at all in ECN 312 or ECN 313, you shouldn't take this class. Pablo is awesome. Very helpful, lectures well, and answers questions. He does talk a lot though. Some information is vital, some he's repeating for the 30th time, which I guess is helpful for some. Do the problem sets.

Pablo is awesome. His door is always open and he answers emails extremely fast as well. Do the "optional" assignments and you will be well prepared for his tests which make up the entirety of your grade. I think 1 of the 4 tests didn't have a perfect score so they are able to be mastered.

Pablo is a genius and knows his stuff. He is not a great teacher. Went to all office hour, didn't help much. Most people dropped or failed. Pablo talks down to the class/can be rude. His lack of understanding of where econ majors at Asu are with set notation/proofs and his refusal to set the course up so students can be successful is disheartening.

This teacher makes this class 10 times harder than it should be. I've been in college/university for a few years now. Out of all the professors I've taken he is the toughest. This teacher simply makes passing any class IMPOSSIBLE!I am currently taking ECN 312 with another teacher and it is 10 times easier.

This professor is easily the WORST I have ever experienced. If you take ECN 416 with him, don't expect to finish the course. He is very unclear in everything he says, has a lot of typos on his powerpoints, and dismisses everything as "simple" or "trivial" He allows you to use all of his powerpoints on exams but they don't help.AVOID HIM IF POSSIBLE

This teacher is the worst teacher ever! Avoid him if you can. You will not need text books in this course, because all the lectures are from ppt but u will not understand the ppt if u dont go to class. He expects everyone to be experts in Calculus, and speeds thru lecture with horrible handwriting. The avg test score is around 40/100. No Homeworks.

Well um, the theory of econ. is pretty easy but this teach tests you on your level of math! If you are proficient in calculus and a lot of notation then you will do good. He speeds thru material, class average going into final was below 40%, if you get below a 60% on final you fail the class, many people did!
This class was actually interesting, and I think actually improved my writing unlike most gen ed english classes. On top of it all McElroy is very easy on the eyes.
Had him as my English 101 prof. and loved it. The class isn't necessarily my favorite but he definitely made this class enjoyable and was always willing to help.

This teacher is awesome.  I would recommend to anyone taking ENG101 to take him if they can he is a very exciting person and he made my mornings much better! not to mention how easy the class is as well!
Very easy and simple class to take. A great teacher who is there for you and is always willing top! Definitely one of the best teachers I have.
An extremely fun and great teacher. I loved going to class even when it was early in the morning.
She is great

Ivy is very nice. She is willing to help if you every have questions. The class I took moves fast, but she was very clear with everything and answered the questions I had. I would highly recommend her. Also, make sure you buy the textbook!

Ivy is fantastic! I'm in SPA 111 which is 101 and 102 combined in to one semester. Because of this, the class moves very fast, but if you are a quick learner I recommend it so you don't have to take 2 sems. She is helpful, but you really need the book for the homework assignments, which are online. Tests are also online b/c 111 is a hybrid course.

Ivy is a really sweet person. She cares about her students and is really easy going. The tests are easy but there's an hour time limit so work quickly. Drops lowest test and quiz scores. Her only downfall is she takes attendance and penalizes 1% of your grade for every absence after the second.
Ivy's great! Doesn't grade too hard and is able to have fun while teaching Spanish. Probably the best Spanish instructor I've had at ASU.

Great guy, but could have done a better job! Took the course online, and the Instructor was no where to be found for more than half of it. Felt like the materials were thrown at us with little organization and little ellaboration. Quizzes were very ambiguous and hard to take. A class that I was excited to take, went south quick! Can be better!!!
Young, Bright, Helpful, Enthusiastic, Very Knowledgeable. I really enjoyed this professor.

There are 10 online assignments that were easy A's. Other than the online homework, there were two tests-midterm and the final. She leaves grading to her TA, and we didn't get our midterm grades until a MONTH after taking the test. She is all over the place in her lectures and the study guide was not helpful. Few Extra Credit opportunities.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Best professor at ASU. Especially if you are actually interested in a career in law. She's inspiring in class and out. (and the classes aren't difficult if you show up, but are super interesting)

Herbert is amazing! Law is a tough subject but she makes it understandable for almost anyone. She has a great upbeat personality that makes me want to show up for class. I signed up for another law class specifically so I could have her again my Senior year. She helps students and gives extra credit
Best law prof at ASU.

Best professor so far. She challenges you intellectually and made you think more. I got both A+s in two of her courses this semester. I wouldn't say it is an easy A+ class, because I put in quite amount of time to study.  I am glad I also learned quite amount of knowledge. Beside class , She is also a nice person.

I rave about Anne because she is an outstanding professor. I have literally taken her classes over and over again because of how amazing of a person she is. Not only does she make your course material understandable but she also makes sure that you are not beating yourself up over difficult reading material. A+ if you listen, show up, participate!

Prof H is great!!! I took this class expecting it to be hard but Prof H made it super easy and understandable. She offered a total of 90 extra credit points over the year. I highly recommend this class!!!

Absolutely hands down THE BEST teacher for Undergraduate Law at ASU She represents O'Connor Law School in an impressive way Just go to class and listen to what she has to say Super intelligent and will go out of her way to help any student at any moment. Sensible and fun Some reading but it should be expected form a law course Done 3 classes all A+

Phenomenal teacher. Go to every lecture and it's impossible to not get an A+. She is so great, I'm taking her 310 class to follow up 210. Excellent class for business law students. I recommend her to everyone
Professor H is the best! Take this class! Topics are really interesting and if you attend class it's an easy A. I'm taking her for 310 I enjoyed her class so much. Other professors.... take notes

Awesome teacher. Uses actual cases and examples for tests to prove you can apply the concepts of the class to a real situation - not hard - actually makes the class interesting and engages you to actually learn the material. Stay on top of assignments

Anne is a great instructor. she's enthusiastic about the subject, brings real world examples, and promotes discussion in the class, even in a big lecture hall. She has personally gone out of her way for me to ensure the best learning environment possible.

Highly recommend his MKT 435 course. We met once weekly, attendance not taken but highly recommended due to the amount of material covered in each lecture. Rarely kept us for the entire class, didn't need a text book, wrote a handful of 1-3 page papers and completed 2 group assignments and a short final exam with open notes. This class was great.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Prof. Denning is very smart, ready to help, and practical with his advice. He's a good person to get to know. As an instructor, he does not make classes overtly difficult. Learning seems to be more of a priority than grading, so to speak.
Professor Denning is outstanding! Class material is simple and very interesting. If you put in time and effort, you will end up with an A!
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--GROUP PROJECTS--Would take again

comment: Wasn't my favorite class, but I think he is a smart guy and cares that we get something out of the class. make sure you enjoy your group because you will be working them all semester.
He's a bit outdated. Might be time to retire or understand the younger generation of business students/professionals.
That was a great experience! He is not simply teaching, he is also mentoring. It is really important because he's got great of a deal of expertise in marketing and is more than ready to share.

One of my favorite teachers at ASU, he will set you up to succeed after school. He is a successful guy with lots of experience, he gets to the point and makes you feel more confident about going into the real world.
Very good lecturer; however, none of his test questions come from his lectures. Overall, this was a great class.

Great Class, he was very organize and made it possible to get a good grade if you did your work and assignment as you are suppose to. Highly recommended. Was very responsive to email. I actually learned some good stuff. 7 Quiz 15 points and a short writing assignment for each. The more I studied the better my grad.Reading the chapter twice worked

Dr. Oswald is easily reachable outside of class. If you have a question, he will sit through an entire assignment and walk you through what needs to be done. Sometimes the theory-based lectures don't correlate to the code-based homework. 1 code homework a week, 3 code projects, 1 written midterm.

He truly wanted his students to pass. He was not able to curve the class so he made review sessions outside of class to help students comprehend. Very personable and lectures are a great time to ask questions. At the same time, quizzes and tests are tough but not unreasonably hard.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: The class has lectures online and in class you do homework problems which is extremely helpful. He really makes it so that you aren't doing the longest possible method for the assignments which is extremely helpful. Difficult course but wants everyone to pass I would definitely take again.
ratingTags: Respected--Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Great professor, really nice and caring. Wants all his students to pass, and really is quite interactive and helpful. We had a backwards classroom, lectures online, homework in class. Exams were easy as I went to class and practiced all the homework. Put in the work and you will pass. Final Exam on the other hand was extremely difficult.
I thought the course was pretty hard, but he is always good about updating piazza at all times of the night. One of the very few down to earth teachers I've had here.

Statics is a mandatory attendance, homework heavy class. Weekly assignments take on average about four hours. There are in class quizzes once a week. Oswald is a funny guy and if you can put up with the first two weeks of lecture it gets interesting afterward. Pay attention to all the methods he teaches, even if they seem unnecessary at the time.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Hilarious

comment: The class is very straightforward in terms of expectations and what you need to do to get an A. If you really want to learn the material you will need to put in extra effort as it will not just fall in your lap.

Only a few criteria are required to rate a Professor as to their abilities as a teacher/mentor. One is is their eagerness to help students learn and the other is their availability outside of class. Dr. Oswald has both of these attributes in spades and is an excellent Professor. His office door is always open, a rarity amongst his SEMTE colleagues.

He was a pretty good professor. I got a B in the class, and I definitely had a good understanding of the material taught. Most of this class is just a review of solid mechanics, so to do well, you just need to know your basics really well. The 3D stuff gets confusing but he tries his best to make you understand. Overall had a good semester.

Professor Oswald is a great professor. He was enthusiastic, knowledgeable, and humorous during lectures. He really wants his students to understand and excel. I would recommend working out more problems, since there are a few with hw/lecture. Labs were tedious. Tests are fair. Homework is challenging. Overall, this was a great class.
Energetic and understanding. Works with you to pass and if something comes up and you miss a quiz he will work with you. Lectures are not boring and he finds ways to apply to real applications.

Oswald is a super nice guy and clearly really knows his stuff. He isn't number one when it comes to making the material easy to understand but he's super willing to work with you in office hoursover email to help you do well. He is also extremely lenient on grading and helpful during office hours. I highly recommend him.

Dr Oswald's class is very straightforwards- what he expects you to do and the work needed to pass or get an A in the class are clearly defined at the start of the semester. He is great at explaining concepts and is mathematically adept, and is willing to help provided you go to office hours. Honors Project with him was fun. Enjoyed the class.
Good Teacher. Willing to Help outside of class. Do your work and you will be fine. Review your book and you will be fine. Very clear in lecture and very fair grader. Once again DO YOUR WORK!

It's true that he's a nice guy, although really has no idea how to teach. It's clear that I was in his first class, so there's hope that he'll learn to teach better as time goes on. He knows the material but just can't communicate it well or break it down conceptually. Luckily the class is pretty easy and you can teach yourself from the book.

Really Nice Guy. Lectures hard to really understand where is going with things sometimes. He was Never sure how he wanted to curve but definitely did. Can tell he is a new teacher but can't say I thought he was bad.

Lectures are basically a restatement of the reading, pretty boring. Expect readings weekly. She's very kind and understanding though, and wants you to succeed. Coursework isn't super relevant to teaching if you don't have/work with ELLs, but it is useful to learn about strategies to use with students who struggle with language in general.
Lots of group work. Never gets things graded. Lectures are pretty boring (but so is the content). Really sweet lady, but the class is pretty useless.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--GROUP PROJECTS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Really great class. She did great with presenting the information that we will need to have as future teachers and how to apply it. Pleasure to be in her class. It was very valuable.

Silva was not a hard grader at all, but she literally didn't know my grade until the last week of school. Class was interesting but I did not learn much. There was one test and it was our midterm. She was very nice and if you do all the assignments, you'll easily get an A.
ratingTags: SO MANY PAPERS--Tests? Not many--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: She didnt do a good job creating a welcoming envorinment. Our class discussions were awkward and quiet because she made this class entirley about her culture. We also had a semester long project that I started working on earlier in the semester but she gave us different guidlines 2 days before we were supposed go present it. I wouldnt recommend.
Lots of reading but good professor. I would take another course by her.
Really easy professor. Don't really learn anything though. Knows what she's talking about and is very understanding.
makes class fun. Great professor
