Knows the subject. Does not respond to email right away, but very understanding, positive, and cares about the topic.

Terrible with grading work/entering grades in a timely manner. Gives very basic feedback and super unclear instructions. Expectations aren't very clear either yet when she grades she finds so many things to point out. Also she responds to emails late, if ever. On the other hand, she is very knowledgeable about the topic and very passionate as well.
Worst teacher I have had at ASU. Very rude and disorganized. I would never take a class with her ever again.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: She's a pretty easy grader but there's a lot of busy work and a good number of group projects as well. Deadlines are occasionally somewhat unclear or announced last-minute, but it's not that big of a deal. She makes an effort to keep the class interactive and engaging.
She is very knowledgeable about the content she teaches. Helpful and definitely a great foundational class to to take with her.
She was so easy. We were assigned to read every week but no one really did. Didnt really learn anything.

If you don't like group projects, AVOID.  The content of the class is all over the place, but she is nice and helpful.  The assignments and projects aren't tough, but there are so many for a college class it starts to feel like busy work after about a month.

Dr. Silva is such an amazing professor,  this is my first BLE class at ASU and I just love it.  Her lectures are fun and the group activities as well. Here classes are always full but the atmosphere is good. I will definitely take her class again.

She is one of the best professors I've ever had. She is extremely passionate about the topic and will make you passionate about it as well. Her class is actually fun and not that hard. I would definitely recommend her for any BLE class you will encounter.

Dr. Silva is awesome! I am currently in my 5th class with her and would recommend her classes to anyone. She is flexible, makes sure that the content is relevant, and works to help you learn the material and become a better teacher. Seriously, she's the best.

I highly recommend this teacher! Very understanding and is always there to help. She is a wonderful teacher and I hope I get to have her as a teacher again. She has a lot of strategies to help students in the class and she is willing to help you succeed in any way. But you have to go to class!!!!!!!

Dr. Silva is awesome. Attendance is MANDATORY! Her class is easy in the sense that the work is not tough, but there are quite a few assignments that are due through the semester. Lots of group work and group discussions. I definitely recommend.

other than 506, this class is critical for understanding control systems. Make sure you learn MATLAB programming as tests and HWs are MATLAB intensive and your performance in this course will very much depend on that. The project on the line following bot was great for understanding the practical use of control systems and PID control.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: Shows interesting applications and at the same time keeps reminding the basic concepts that are important as engineers. Encourages interaction and gives great advice and feedback. Helps you plan your coursework if you ask him. All in all, he wants to see people glean knowledge and if you are committed, he will help you like no one else.

Easily the best lecturer I have had in ASU. Walks you through the concepts step by step and encourages interaction. If you are truly interested in learning control theory and robotics you can learn so much from him! Assignments are designed for you to work for the results but the amount of work is reasonable.

If you're specializing in robotics or controls, take all his classes! Lectures are well structured and if you study diligently, you will learn a lot! Very important for the industry. The grading is well split between HWs, project, and exams.
clear explanation of the materials, give real world examples, best professor I met!
His classes are tough. His exams are tougher. Homeworks are no way related to his exams.

One of the most interesting classes I've taken at ASU. He is very clear cut on grading and extra credit.
